They sell a fine percale sheet at a really modest price.

116
00:08:47,610 --> 00:08:51,614
卡塞尔夫人，告诉我，你和查理还睡双人床吗?
Tell me, Mrs. Castle, do you and Charlie still use a double bed?

117
00:08:51,740 --> 00:08:54,993
或者这是个愚蠢的问题，因为你们现在已经分居了?
Or is that a foolish question, since you're separated now?

118
00:08:55,118 --> 00:08:57,537
你们分居了，是吗?
You are separated, aren't you?

119
00:08:57,662 --> 00:09:00,623
帕蒂，你真是太有毅力了。
Patty, you sure take the cake for persistence.

120
00:09:00,749 --> 00:09:04,210
我们都是理智、老练的人。穿绉布也没用。
We're all sensible, sophisticated people. There's no use wearing crepe.

121
00:09:04,335 --> 00:09:08,548
去年这个国家有40多万起离婚案件。
There were over 400,000 divorce cases in this country last year.

122
00:09:08,673 --> 00:09:11,051
它就像普通的感冒一样普遍。
It's getting as common as the ordinary head cold.

123
00:09:11,176 --> 00:09:13,428
也许你是对的，本尼迪克特小姐。
You know, you may be right, miss Benedict.

124
00:09:13,553 --> 00:09:15,263
然而，我觉得这很悲哀。
However, I find it sad.

125
00:09:16,473 --> 00:09:18,725
我们的私人生活与你无关。
And our personal life is not your affair.

126
00:09:18,850 --> 00:09:25,398
-你是那个会告诉我的孩子。-马里恩…我才是这个镇子里敢于告诉你少管闲事的人。
- And you're the child who'll tell me. - Marion... I'm the one in this town who's not afraid to tell you to mind your own business.

127
00:09:26,107 --> 00:09:29,277
好吧，我很高兴我们达成了谅解。
All right, I'm glad we've come to an understanding.

128
00:09:29,402 --> 00:09:30,904
——现在,帕蒂……-别大惊小怪，恰克。
- Now, Patty... - No fuss, Chuck.

129
00:09:31,029 --> 00:09:33,531
我知道我什么时候不受欢迎了。我知道这一点。
I know when I've worn out my welcome. I'm aware of that.

130
00:09:33,656 --> 00:09:34,991
皮特的缘故!
For Pete's sake!

131
00:09:35,116 --> 00:09:38,578
埃斯，你最好做点什么，否则我们都要完蛋了。
Ace, you'd better do something, or we'll all end up the creek.

132
00:09:41,081 --> 00:09:43,291
听着，小天使你以为你在干什么?
Look, angel what do you think you're doing?

133
00:09:43,416 --> 00:09:46,169
她不会在我家里跟我耍花招的。
She doesn't play madam pry with me, not in my own house.

134
00:09:49,255 --> 00:09:50,507
帕蒂,等等!
Patty, wait!

135
00:09:51,508 --> 00:09:55,720
我是做电影的。我不能承受你对正直的猛烈攻击。
I'm in the movie business. I can't afford your acute attacks of integrity.

136
00:09:55,845 --> 00:09:58,056
你跟她说话的方式!
Oh, the way you talk to her!

137
00:09:58,973 --> 00:10:00,850
——这是怎么回事?——液体蜂蜜。
- How's that? - Liquid honey.

138
00:10:00,975 --> 00:10:05,188
-哦，我对她不真诚。-丈夫，对我虚情假意吧。
- Oh, I'm insincere with her. - Husband, be insincere with me.

139
00:10:05,313 --> 00:10:06,731
帕蒂有1800万读者。
Patty's got 18 million readers.

140
00:10:06,856 --> 00:10:08,691
为什么她对抗?意义在哪里?
Why antagonize her? Where's the sense?

141
00:10:08,817 --> 00:10:11,486
有时候，我相信完全没有知觉。
From time to time, I believe in being completely senseless.

142
00:10:11,611 --> 00:10:13,530
我是个女人，不是外交官。
I'm a woman, not a diplomat.

143
00:10:13,655 --> 00:10:16,491
你对她说"上帝保佑"的方式!
The way you said "god bless" to that one!

144
00:10:16,616 --> 00:10:18,952
我还以为你会想吐呢。
I should think it'd make you want to throw up.

145
00:10:19,077 --> 00:10:21,079
当然，你并不真诚。
Of course, you're not sincere.

146
00:10:23,748 --> 00:10:25,500
你过得怎么样?
How have you been?

147
00:10:26,334 --> 00:10:28,086
很好。很好。
Fine. Just fine.

148
00:10:30,255 --> 00:10:33,007
我开始喜欢这张照片了。
You know, I'm beginning to like this picture.

149
00:10:33,883 --> 00:10:35,885
可以进入奥运代表队。
Could make the olympic team.

150
00:10:39,472 --> 00:10:42,725
关于这个rouault，你说得对。他那么做。
You're right about this rouault guy. He broods.

151
00:10:42,851 --> 00:10:50,024
有一定的品质。我不知道…这几天我看了很多次。
There's a certain quality. I don't know... I've been looking at it a lot the last few days.

152
00:10:50,900 --> 00:10:53,153
有时候，当我最近一个人的时候…
Sometimes, when I'm alone lately...

153
00:10:56,698 --> 00:10:59,742
一个老小丑在等待，等待继续。
An old clown waiting in the wings, waiting to go on.

154
00:10:59,868 --> 00:11:02,245
跳几下，让他们大吃一惊。
Cut a few capers, knock 'em dead.

155
00:11:03,872 --> 00:11:06,541
但他已经做过无数次了。
But he's done it a million times.

156
00:11:07,876 --> 00:11:10,336
它已经没有任何意义了。
It doesn't mean anything anymore.

157
00:11:16,968 --> 00:11:19,721
-极强的?——没有。
- Too fortissimo? - No.

158
00:11:24,809 --> 00:11:26,769
我会把它买回来。
I'd buy it all back.

159
00:11:30,231 --> 00:11:35,195
比利怎么样?我已经两周没见到他了。
How's Billy? I haven't seen him for two weeks.

160
00:11:35,820 --> 00:11:38,823
——三个星期。-好吧，三周。
- Three weeks. - Okay, three weeks.

161
00:11:39,199 --> 00:11:40,575
他感冒了。
He has a cold.

162
00:11:42,327 --> 00:11:44,204
——发烧?——嗯。
- Fever? - Uh-uh.

163
00:11:44,329 --> 00:11:48,791
但是，你知道，它一直在。你就是不能让他远离大海。
But, you know, it hangs on. You just can't keep him out of the ocean.

164
00:11:53,129 --> 00:11:56,049
-在海滩上寂寞吗?——是的。
- Is it lonely at the beach? - Yes.

165
00:11:58,051 --> 00:12:02,597
——非常孤独?-查理，别开始了。
- Very lonely? - Charlie, don't start this, please.

166
00:12:02,722 --> 00:12:04,557
回来吧，天使，我可以改变。
Come back, angel, I can change.

167
00:12:04,682 --> 00:12:07,310
你如何改变?你这样太久了。
How can you change? You've been this way for so long.

168
00:12:07,435 --> 00:12:09,312
我能。你一定要相信我。
I can. You've got to believe me on this.

169
00:12:09,437 --> 00:12:12,065
在此之前，我相信过你很多次。
I have believed you before this, any number of times.

170
00:12:12,190 --> 00:12:16,027
-你不会认为那些偶尔出现的女孩…-是的，我确实认为那些偶遇的女孩!
- You don't think those occasional girls... - Yes, I do think those occasional girls!

171
00:12:16,152 --> 00:12:17,570
惊讶吗?
Surprised?

172
00:12:18,279 --> 00:12:19,489
查理!
Charlie!

173
00:12:19,614 --> 00:12:23,201
男人的生活只有两种方式，要么结婚，要么像单身汉一样。
A man can live only one of two ways, either married or like a bachelor.

174
00:12:23,326 --> 00:12:27,872
你想要的是两者中最好的!在我看来，那不是婚姻。
What you want is the best of both! And that's not a marriage, not in my book.

175
00:12:31,626 --> 00:12:36,005
查理·卡斯……他是个奇迹。
Charlie cass... He was a wonder.

176
00:12:36,756 --> 00:12:38,675
我是凯斯太太。
I was Mrs. Cass.

177
00:12:39,801 --> 00:12:42,303
现在你是霍夫的卡塞尔先生了。
Now you're hoff's Mr. Castle.

178
00:12:42,428 --> 00:12:46,307
哦,来吧!我不信。我不属于斯坦利·霍夫!
Oh, come on! I don't buy that. I don't belong to Stanley hoff!

179
00:12:46,432 --> 00:12:47,892
——不是吗?——不!我是自由球员!
- No? - No! I'm a free agent!

180
00:12:48,017 --> 00:12:49,978
你打算和他签新合同吗?
Are you going to sign his new contract?

181
00:12:50,103 --> 00:12:52,897
玛丽恩，我想让你回到我身边。
Marion, I want you to come back home to me.

182
00:12:53,022 --> 00:12:54,691
-就这样?——是的。
- Just like that? - Yes.

183
00:12:54,816 --> 00:13:00,613
我还不够完美，但如果你以为自己能独自面对这个广阔的世界，那你就错了。
I'm far from perfect, but you're making a mistake if you think you can face this big, wide world alone.

184
00:13:01,322 --> 00:13:05,368
别告诉我你有比利，因为他还是四口就能吃下一颗葡萄。
Don't tell me you've got Billy, because he still eats a grape in four bites.

185
00:13:05,493 --> 00:13:07,078
没有我，你就没有家。
Without me, you don't have a family.

186
00:13:07,203 --> 00:13:10,498
你连个朋友都没有，除非是汉克·缇格。
You don't even have a friend, unless it's Hank teagle.

187
00:13:10,623 --> 00:13:13,209
汉克早在成为你的朋友之前就是我的朋友。
Hank was my friend long before he was yours.

188
00:13:14,919 --> 00:13:17,714
汉克昨晚向我求婚了。
Hank asked me to marry him last night.

189
00:13:17,839 --> 00:13:19,173
然后呢?
And?

190
00:13:20,633 --> 00:13:22,969
你说什么?
What did you say?

191
00:13:23,094 --> 00:13:24,679
我能说什么呢?
What could I say?

192
00:13:26,848 --> 00:13:28,558
他有勇气。
He's got his nerve.

193
00:13:28,683 --> 00:13:31,728
-他只说了"如果"——如果?
- All he said was "if". - If?

194
00:13:31,853 --> 00:13:33,146
如果,如果,如果!
If, if, if!

195
00:13:33,271 --> 00:13:35,648
我不想跟你谈这个，不是吗?
I tried to avoid this conversation, didn't I?

196
00:13:35,773 --> 00:13:39,152
好吧,你赢了。名人丈夫说:“你赢了。”
Okay, you win. Famous husband remarks, "you win."

197
00:13:40,278 --> 00:13:42,322
拜托，别像个家庭主妇。
Please, don't be such a housewife.

198
00:13:42,447 --> 00:13:45,867
别碰那讨厌的眼镜!我们花钱请人来做这件事!
Leave the lousy glasses alone! We pay somebody to do that!

199
00:13:45,992 --> 00:13:47,243
罗素!
Russell!

200
00:13:58,171 --> 00:14:04,135
看……我手表的烂表带也断了。
Look... The lousy strap's broken on my watch, too.

201
00:14:10,725 --> 00:14:13,227
我需要周一的支票。
I'll be needing a check for Monday.

202
00:14:13,353 --> 00:14:15,313
账单堆积如山。
The bills are piling up.

203
00:14:16,814 --> 00:14:20,193
好吧，我会让哈罗德从办公室寄过来的。
All right, I'll have Harold send it from the office.

204
00:14:34,123 --> 00:14:36,542
为什么,Castle太太。我没听见你进来。
Why, Mrs. Castle. I didn't hear you come in.

205
00:14:36,667 --> 00:14:39,045
-很高兴见到你。-谢谢你，拉塞尔。
- This is a real pleasure. - Thank you, Russell.

206
00:14:39,170 --> 00:14:41,339
一切顺利吗?
Everything running all right?

207
00:14:41,464 --> 00:14:44,717
像丝绸一样光滑，卡塞尔夫人。很好。
Smooth as silk, Mrs. Castle. Just fine.

208
00:14:44,842 --> 00:14:46,803
这很好。我走之前再见你。
That's good. I'll see you before I leave.

209
00:14:46,928 --> 00:14:48,137
谢谢你！
Thank you.

210
00:14:49,097 --> 00:14:52,308
-你能把这个拿出来吗?——是的,女士。
- Oh, would you mind taking this out? - Yes, ma'am.

211
00:14:58,356 --> 00:14:59,816
查理?
Charlie?

212
00:15:03,528 --> 00:15:05,488
你要不要和霍夫重修旧好?
Are you renewing with hoff or not?

213
00:15:05,613 --> 00:15:07,824
汉克哪来的胆量向你求婚?
Where does Hank get the nerve to propose to you?

214
00:15:07,949 --> 00:15:11,119
忘记汉克。他两周后要去纽约。
Forget about Hank. He's leaving for New York in two weeks.

215
00:15:11,244 --> 00:15:13,162
去找40美分的杜松子酒?
To find a 40-cent gin?

216
00:15:13,287 --> 00:15:16,582
他正在写一部新小说。他戒酒好几周了。
He's writing a new novel. He's been on the wagon for weeks.

217
00:15:17,542 --> 00:15:20,253
听着，你说你想让我回到你身边。
Look, you say you want me to come back to you.

218
00:15:20,378 --> 00:15:23,756
相信我，我不会，永远不会，只要你签了那份合同。
Well, believe me, I won't, not ever, if you sign that contract.

219
00:15:23,881 --> 00:15:25,133
哦,那了!
Oh, that again!

220
00:15:25,258 --> 00:15:30,221
我从没想过有一天一笔敲定的交易会让你不寒而栗!
I never expected to see the day when a firm deal would give you chills and fever!

221
00:15:30,346 --> 00:15:33,141
我也不知道，我和下一个一样也是人。
Neither did I. I'm as human as the next one.

222
00:15:33,266 --> 00:15:37,395
这是一笔极好的交易，但有效期是七年，以及随之而来的生活。
It's a fabulous deal, but it's for seven years, and the life that goes with it.

223
00:15:37,520 --> 00:15:40,148
或者我该说随之而来的死亡?
Or should I say the death that goes with it?

224
00:15:40,273 --> 00:15:44,193
看看你自己。你现在已经半死了。
Look at yourself. You're half-dead right now.

225
00:15:44,318 --> 00:15:46,320
我好多年没见你这么神采飞扬了。
I haven't seen you sparkle in years.

226
00:15:46,446 --> 00:15:49,532
你在别人面前装模作样，但我是你妻子，我知道。
You put on a show for other people, but I'm your wife, I know it.

227
00:15:50,158 --> 00:15:57,415
查理,我的查理…你的思想，你的精神，你的灵魂都怎么了?
Charlie, my Charlie... What's happened to your mind, your spirit, your soul?

228
00:15:57,540 --> 00:15:59,834
查理·卡斯，我嫁的那个人。
Charlie cass, the guy I married.

229
00:15:59,959 --> 00:16:02,378
他是一只老虎。他喜欢争论。
He was a tiger. He liked to argue.

230
00:16:02,712 --> 00:16:07,133
因为你有信仰，你为之奋斗。
Because you believed in things, and what you believed in, you fought for.

231
00:16:07,258 --> 00:16:09,177
这是查理·卡斯。
And that was Charlie cass.

232
00:16:10,928 --> 00:16:12,805
你现在相信什么?
What do you believe in now?

233
00:16:14,640 --> 00:16:22,899
你想要什么?就像那个在沃尔格林药店喝着咖啡，对着剧院的悲惨状况大吼大叫的孩子吗?
What do you want? The wild-eyed kid I was, nursing a cup of coffee in walgreens, yelling about the sad state of the theatre?

234
00:16:23,024 --> 00:16:25,735
我告诉你我不想要什么。
I'll tell you what I don't want.

235
00:16:25,860 --> 00:16:32,158
我可不想让一个愚蠢的，满座的家伙坐在杜松子酒桌旁，交换电话号码和最新消息!
I don't want one of those witless, sold-out guys sitting around a gin table, swapping phone numbers and the latest dirt!

236
00:16:32,283 --> 00:16:33,659
哦，你说得真好。
Oh, how you talk.

237
00:16:33,784 --> 00:16:36,954
查理，我不想你签那份合同。
Charlie, I don't want you to sign that contract.

238
00:16:37,079 --> 00:16:38,956
你给了制片厂一磅肉。
You've given the studio their pound of flesh.

239
00:16:39,081 --> 00:16:42,919
我是霍夫联邦最大的明星。我每年对他们来说值几百万。
I'm hoff-federated's biggest star. I'm worth millions a year to them.

240
00:16:43,044 --> 00:16:46,714
-他不让我走。你知道为什么。-告诉他你要离开好莱坞。
- He won't let me go. You know why. - Tell him you're leaving Hollywood.

241
00:16:46,839 --> 00:16:48,841
保证不给别人拍电影。
Promise never to make pictures for anyone else.

242
00:16:48,966 --> 00:16:51,093
很好。我该怎么办?电视、玩吗?
Fine. What do I do? TV, a play?

243
00:16:51,219 --> 00:16:55,223
剧院是一个流血的残垣。你得等好几年才能得到一个像样的角色。
The theatre's a bleeding stump. You gotta wait years for one decent part.

244
00:16:55,348 --> 00:16:58,684
不管怎样，这是什么鬼话?
And anyhow, what is all this arty bunk?

245
00:16:58,809 --> 00:17:03,147
你知道这个行业有能力拍出好电影，有勇气和意义的电影。
You know this industry is capable of turning out good pictures, pictures with guts and meaning.

246
00:17:03,272 --> 00:17:06,526
当然，当然，我们认识一些这样做的人。
Sure, sure, and we know some of the men who do it.

247
00:17:06,651 --> 00:17:15,576
斯蒂文斯，曼凯维奇，喀山，休斯顿，威勒，怀尔德，斯坦利·克莱默，但没有斯坦利·霍夫!
Stevens, mankiewicz, kazan, huston, wyler, Wilder, Stanley Kramer, but never Stanley hoff!

248
00:17:15,701 --> 00:17:18,871
从来没有!不是一次!不管他的命怎么样!
Never! Not once! Not for the life of him!

249
00:17:18,996 --> 00:17:21,499
不是为了那些浮夸的媒体声明!
Not for all the pompous press statements!

250
00:17:21,624 --> 00:17:25,878
斯坦利·霍夫将亲自制作托尔斯泰的《战争与和平》!
Stanley hoff will personally produce 'war and peace' by Tolstoy!

251
00:17:26,003 --> 00:17:27,213
要有那么一天就好了。
That'll be the day.

252
00:17:27,338 --> 00:17:34,637
主演查理·卡塞尔一手拿着长鞭……和…另一个是漂白过的金发女郎。
Starring Charlie castle with a bullwhip in one hand... And... a bleached blonde in the other.

253
00:17:36,305 --> 00:17:39,267
哦……查理。
Oh... Charlie.

254
00:17:40,059 --> 00:17:42,186
请过来一下。
Come here, please.

255
00:17:45,398 --> 00:17:48,776
亲爱的，这个世界上永远都有斯坦利·霍夫。
Darling, there'll always be Stanley hoffs in this world.

256
00:17:48,901 --> 00:17:51,946
不只是在电影行业，而是在所有地方。
Not just in the movie industry, but everywhere.

257
00:17:52,780 --> 00:17:59,829
他总是一个蔑视体面和人类尊严的人，想把你也拖下水。
Always one who, just by his contempt for decency and human dignity, tries to drag you down with them.

258
00:18:00,621 --> 00:18:02,373
查理,不。
Charlie, no.

259
00:18:02,498 --> 00:18:08,045
我是霍夫的囚犯和天使，签署这份合同就是赎金。
I'm hoff's prisoner and angel, and signing this contract is the ransom fee.

260
00:18:08,170 --> 00:18:10,715
那天晚上我没有勇气。
I didn't have the nerve that night.

261
00:18:11,924 --> 00:18:15,386
-我做了错误的决定。-那晚我们做了错误的决定。
- I made the wrong decision. - We made the wrong decision that night.

262
00:18:15,511 --> 00:18:19,390
-我应该朝另一边走。-亲爱的，我们都失败了。
- I should've swung the other way. - Darling, we both failed.

263
00:18:20,516 --> 00:18:23,894
我应该从自怜中挣脱出来，推你一把。
I should've snapped out of my self-pity and shoved you.

264
00:18:24,895 --> 00:18:28,691
但我们还有第二次机会。我知道这是一场赌博。
But we have a second chance. It's a gamble, I know.

265
00:18:28,816 --> 00:18:31,193
我知道如果你拒绝签字霍夫会怎么做。
I know what hoff can do if you refuse to sign.

266
00:18:31,319 --> 00:18:35,364
-你以为你知道。-查理，他只是个普通人。
- You think you know. - Charlie, he's only a man.

267
00:18:35,489 --> 00:18:38,618
他不是神，他不会在愤怒中杀死我们。
He's not god, to strike us down in his wrath.

268
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:48,461
你真想把它扔掉吗?
You really want to throw this away?

269
00:18:48,586 --> 00:18:55,468
我知道我说的是你辉煌的事业以及随之而来的一切，但是拒绝他，查理，拒绝他。
I know I'm talking about your fabulous career and all that goes with it, but refuse him, Charlie, turn him down.

270
00:18:55,593 --> 00:18:57,053
好吧……
Alright...

271
00:18:59,221 --> 00:19:00,681
”| | |试一试。
|'|| try.

272
00:19:02,058 --> 00:19:06,062
我还没同意签字呢。我已经拖延了几周，几个月。
I haven't actually agreed to sign. I've been stalling for weeks, for months.

273
00:19:06,979 --> 00:19:10,149
nat要过来了。也许他能想出一个好主意。
And nat's coming by. Maybe he can come up with a big idea.

274
00:19:10,274 --> 00:19:13,611
我很喜欢nat，他很善良。
I'm very fond of nat, he's good and kind.

275
00:19:13,736 --> 00:19:16,322
但这次你只能靠自己了。
But you'll have to fight this one by yourself.

276
00:19:16,447 --> 00:19:19,158
-可能行不通。-就看你的了。
- It may not work. - It's in your hands.

277
00:19:25,665 --> 00:19:33,589
我们的爱。我的意思是……我们彼此相爱，不是吗?这是关键，重要的一点。
We do love. I mean... We do love each other, don't we? That's the thing, the big thing.

278
00:19:33,714 --> 00:19:35,383
我需要你。
I need you.

279
00:19:35,508 --> 00:19:38,594
我要你把斯坦利·霍夫撕成碎片，老虎。
I want you to tear Stanley hoff apart, tiger.

280
00:19:42,556 --> 00:19:45,059
——嗨,尼克。——你好,马里昂。
- Hi, Nicky. - Hello, Marion.

281
00:19:45,184 --> 00:19:48,020
噢,呃…希望我没有打扰到重要的事情。
Oh, er... I hope I'm not interrupting anything important.

282
00:19:48,145 --> 00:19:49,939
是的，但没关系。
You are, but it's all right.

283
00:19:50,064 --> 00:19:52,441
查理……该给他按摩了，马里昂。
Charlie... It's time for his rub, Marion.

284
00:19:52,566 --> 00:19:54,443
-哦，那可以等。-不，不行。
- Oh, that can wait. - No, it can't.

285
00:19:54,568 --> 00:19:56,278
他马上就出来，尼基。
He'll be right out, Nicky.

286
00:19:56,404 --> 00:19:59,532
老虎，我要你身体健康，身体健康。
Tiger, I want you in condition, in the pink.

287
00:20:00,116 --> 00:20:03,452
我有一大堆事情要做，晚饭前还要搬家。
I have a million things to do, and a household to move by suppertime.

288
00:20:03,577 --> 00:20:05,287
——家庭?——确定。
- Household? - Sure.

289
00:20:05,413 --> 00:20:09,125
我，比利，还有这一切。我们是你的，不是吗?
Me, Billy, the whole shebang. We're yours, aren't we?

290
00:20:21,679 --> 00:20:23,597
我稍后再打给你。
I'll call you later.

291
00:20:24,265 --> 00:20:26,100
再见。
See you later.

292
00:20:27,685 --> 00:20:28,978
再见,老虎。
Goodbye, tiger.

293
00:20:29,103 --> 00:20:30,354
再见。
Good bye.

294
00:20:35,025 --> 00:20:37,570
第八大道，雅各布海滩。
Eighth Avenue, Jacob's beach.

295
00:20:38,821 --> 00:20:41,532
你和我，去圣尼克。
You and me, going to St. Nick's.

296
00:20:41,657 --> 00:20:42,950
是的,当然。
Yeah, sure.

297
00:20:43,075 --> 00:20:45,077
你的经纪人来了。
Oh, there's your agent.

298
00:20:45,202 --> 00:20:48,247
嘿,nat !你在那干什么，nat，老家伙?
Hey, nat! What are you doing there, nat, old kid?

299
00:20:48,372 --> 00:20:51,751
,先生们!-你说呢?
- Gentlemen! - What do you say, huh?

300
00:20:55,087 --> 00:20:57,923
——查理。-不，我很油腻，你会弄脏的。
- Charlie. - No, I'm greasy, you'll get all dirty.

301
00:20:58,048 --> 00:21:02,136
娜特，等我做完了，我来锻炼一下你的肩膀怎么样?
Say, nat, when I'm through, how about me working that shoulder of yours?

302
00:21:02,261 --> 00:21:05,931
尼基，你很贴心，但医生说要做透热和打针。
Nicky, you're a sweetheart, but the doctor says diathermy and shots.

303
00:21:06,056 --> 00:21:08,058
没有摩擦。
No friction.

304
00:21:08,184 --> 00:21:10,561
啊,滑囊炎。
Ah, bursitis.

305
00:21:10,686 --> 00:21:13,856
这一行的流行趋势是什么?溃疡。
What's the fashion in the industry? Ulcers.

306
00:21:13,981 --> 00:21:16,734
愤怒。我得了滑囊炎。
The rage. I get bursitis.

307
00:21:16,859 --> 00:21:21,447
但谢谢你，尼基，你想帮忙真是个绅士。
But thank you, Nicky, you are a true gentleman for wanting to help.

308
00:21:22,782 --> 00:21:24,575
口渴时喝水。
Water when you're thirsty.

309
00:21:26,869 --> 00:21:30,706
别跑题了，我今天早上见过你们的业务经理。
Not to digress, I saw your business manager this morning.

310
00:21:30,831 --> 00:21:32,041
哈罗德?
Harold?

311
00:21:32,166 --> 00:21:35,127
他说你是个坏孩子。他没有批准的检查。
He says you're being a bad boy. Checks he didn't approve.

312
00:21:35,252 --> 00:21:39,256
我该怎么做，问艾森豪威尔我能不能塞给一个饥饿的骑手200块?
What am I supposed to do, ask eisenhower if I can slip a hungry rider $200?

313
00:21:39,381 --> 00:21:41,217
这不是我的问题。
That's the least of my problems.

314
00:21:41,342 --> 00:21:44,595
问题。生活充满了问题。他们的工作。
Problems. Life is all problems. They work out.

315
00:21:44,720 --> 00:21:48,766
我有个宝贝要给你，小娜。玛丽恩坚决反对合同。
Well, I've got a honey for you, nat. Marion's dead set against the contract.

316
00:21:48,891 --> 00:21:50,351
我要去找她。
Her, I'm going to talk to.

317
00:21:50,851 --> 00:21:53,229
你不用告诉那个老头。
You don't have to tell the old man.

318
00:21:54,271 --> 00:21:58,442
你们俩真是甜蜜的凡人。我知道她有点忙乱。
You two are such sweet mortals. I know she's a little hectic.

319
00:21:58,567 --> 00:22:02,863
我不想签。我怕如果我这么做，会失去我的家庭。
I don't want to sign it. I'm afraid if I do, it'll cost me my family.

320
00:22:02,988 --> 00:22:05,115
听着，玛丽安会冷静下来的，查理。
Look, Marion will cool down, Charlie.

321
00:22:05,241 --> 00:22:08,994
-我会和她谈谈，你签…-我说的话你一句也没听见，对吧?
- I'll talk to her and you'll sign the... - You don't hear one thing I say, do you?

322
00:22:09,119 --> 00:22:10,538
——没有!——亲爱的,听着。
- Nothing! - Darling, listen.

323
00:22:10,663 --> 00:22:13,624
听?我为什么要听?你从来不听我的!
Listen? Why should I listen? You never listen to me!

324
00:22:18,712 --> 00:22:19,880
现在我在听。
I'm listening now.

325
00:22:20,005 --> 00:22:22,007
我不想签合同!
I don't want to sign the contract!

326
00:22:23,008 --> 00:22:25,010
——你不?-不，我不喜欢。
- You don't? - No, I don't.

327
00:22:26,053 --> 00:22:30,307
-我以为你已经同意签了。-倾听不代表同意。
- I thought you agreed to sign it. - Listening doesn't mean agreement.

328
00:22:30,432 --> 00:22:33,853
我听斯坦利的话，我听你的话，我听得脸色发青。
I listen to Stanley, I listen to you, I listen till I'm blue in the face.

329
00:22:33,978 --> 00:22:36,438
但我不同意签那份合同。
But I did not agree to sign that contract.

330
00:22:38,899 --> 00:22:42,653
我不能再拍那些恶心的电影了。
I can't keep doing those lousy pictures.

331
00:22:42,778 --> 00:22:46,824
但合同上白纸黑字写的。你不必这么做。
But it's in the contract, black on white. You don't have to.

332
00:22:46,949 --> 00:22:50,953
在你看到剧本之前，我就批准并确保剧本是好的。
I approve and make sure the scripts are good, before you even see them.

333
00:22:51,078 --> 00:22:55,541
我是久经沙场的查理·卡塞尔。
This is Charlie "been-around- a-long-time" castle you're talking to.

334
00:22:55,666 --> 00:22:58,210
现在，来吧，给我想个办法。
Now, come on, give, think me a way out.

335
00:22:59,128 --> 00:23:12,141
亲爱的，首先我得告诉你，斯坦利今早让我去他办公室谈合同谈了两个小时，跟哥伦比亚打了招呼，结果就是他们要来这里。
Well, darling, first I ought to tell you Stanley had me in his office about the contract this morning for two hours, hail Columbia, which all leads to the fact that they're dropping in here.

336
00:23:14,727 --> 00:23:17,605
——在这里吗?- Stanley hoff和smiley coy。
- Here? - Stanley hoff and smiley coy.

337
00:23:17,730 --> 00:23:20,608
——什么时候?-随时都可能。
- When? - Any minute now.

338
00:23:20,733 --> 00:23:25,446
邀请你去看比赛，但这将是一场摊牌。
To invite you to the races, but it's going to be a showdown.

339
00:23:25,571 --> 00:23:27,448
尼克,酒精。
Nick, the alcohol.

340
00:23:27,573 --> 00:23:30,326
小娜，你得把我弄出去。
Nat, you've got to get me out of this.

341
00:23:30,451 --> 00:23:34,079
亲爱的，我非常担心。
Darling, I'm terribly worried.

342
00:23:34,204 --> 00:23:37,833
大家都以为你很坚强。
Everybody has got the delusion that you're very tough.

343
00:23:37,958 --> 00:23:40,210
他们把你和你扮演的角色搞混了。
They mix you up with the parts you play.

344
00:23:40,336 --> 00:23:43,047
但我更了解你。
But I know you better.

345
00:23:43,172 --> 00:23:45,841
你是一个特别的理想主义者。
You're a special, idealistic type.

346
00:23:45,966 --> 00:23:49,511
唯一的问题是，商业和理想主义，不能混为一谈。
The only thing is, business and idealism, they don't mix.

347
00:23:49,637 --> 00:23:51,263
这是油和水。
It's oil and water.

348
00:23:51,388 --> 00:23:54,934
电影对你来说不是电影，而是福音。
A movie is not a movie to you, it's a gospel.

349
00:23:55,059 --> 00:24:00,773
但是你错了，亲爱的先生和朋友，总的来说……Nat,闭嘴!请闭嘴!
But you're mistaken, dear sir and friend, in all... Nat, shut up! Please, shut up!

350
00:24:00,898 --> 00:24:03,525
尼基，去房子那边。到那房子里去!
Nicky, go up to the house. Go up to the house!

351
00:24:08,405 --> 00:24:10,908
希腊人能做点什么吗?
Is there anything a Greek can do?

352
00:24:13,410 --> 00:24:17,206
去房子那边，尼基。他们到了就通知我。
Go up to the house, Nicky. Let me know when they get here.

353
00:24:20,125 --> 00:24:21,877
谢谢,性格。
Thanks, character.

354
00:24:28,717 --> 00:24:31,845
查理，说几句重要的话。
Charlie, a few important words.

355
00:24:31,971 --> 00:24:39,353
我们现在不是在和斯坦利讨价还价，但我愿意做任何你让我做的事，在我的能力范围内，因为仁慈的上帝坐在上面。
We are not in a bargaining position with Stanley, but I'd do anything you ask me, within my power, as the good lord sits above.

356
00:24:39,478 --> 00:24:41,438
把我弄出去，小娜。
Just get me out of here, nat.

357
00:24:41,563 --> 00:24:43,649
斯坦利不让你走。
Stanley wouldn't let you go.

358
00:24:44,525 --> 00:24:48,070
如果我撕毁合同，我们搬走呢?
Suppose I just tore up the contract, and we moved away?

359
00:24:48,195 --> 00:24:50,531
-他会怎么做?——是的。他会怎么做呢?
- What would he do? - Yes. What would he do?

360
00:24:52,366 --> 00:24:55,160
上帝禁止他做任何事。
God forbid what he would do.

361
00:24:55,285 --> 00:24:58,956
查理，永远不要因为你不喜欢一个男人而低估他。
Charlie, never underestimate a man because you don't like him.

362
00:24:59,081 --> 00:25:03,335
在斯坦利每天修指甲之前我就认识他了。
I know Stanley since before he had his fingers manicured every day.

363
00:25:03,460 --> 00:25:05,921
他会怎么做。
What he would do.

364
00:25:07,172 --> 00:25:09,717
我们别无选择，查理。
We've got no choice, Charlie.

365
00:25:09,842 --> 00:25:13,887
你知道他有什么把柄。我们不谈的那件事?
You know what he's got on you. That thing we don't talk about?

366
00:25:15,514 --> 00:25:20,519
亲爱的……签字，否则就进监狱。
Darling... You sign, or you go to jail.

367
00:25:23,313 --> 00:25:26,900
他们在这里!霍夫先生和笑脸忸怩!
They're here! Mr. Hoff and smiley coy!

368
00:25:35,284 --> 00:25:38,287
任何方法都是一种死亡方式，对吧?
Every way is a way to die, huh?

369
00:25:38,412 --> 00:25:41,832
我老了。每一种方式都是一种生活方式。
I'm older. Every way is a way to live.

370
00:25:43,625 --> 00:25:45,627
我希望你是对的，娜特。
I hope you're right, nat.

371
00:25:47,796 --> 00:25:51,300
绝对没有。你知道的，霍夫先生。
Absolutely nothing. You know how it is, Mr. Hoff.

372
00:25:51,425 --> 00:25:54,303
有些拳手很厉害，能听到声音，但我不是。
Some fighters, they get punchy, they hear things, but not me.

373
00:25:54,428 --> 00:25:56,972
Nang-nang-nang !见到你,尼克。
Nang-nang-nang! See you, Nick.

374
00:25:58,682 --> 00:26:00,017
啊哈!
A-ha!

375
00:26:01,518 --> 00:26:04,063
两个头在一顶帽子下。这里发生了什么?
Two heads under one hat. What goes on here?

376
00:26:04,188 --> 00:26:07,191
你好吗，斯坦利?笑脸吗?
How are you, Stanley? Smiley?

377
00:26:07,941 --> 00:26:10,611
小娜老是烦我，我都不和他打招呼了。
Nat's in my hair so frequently, I don't say hello to him.

378
00:26:10,736 --> 00:26:12,529
没想到会在这找到你，小娜。
I didn't expect to find you here, nat.

379
00:26:12,654 --> 00:26:15,365
我只是在上帝的阳光下进来，仅此而已。
I just came in out of god's sunshine, that's all.

380
00:26:15,491 --> 00:26:19,078
-你今天早上是怎么醒来的，凯蒂?-我没醒，我醒过来了。
- How'd you wake up this morning, kitty? - I didn't wake up, I came to.

381
00:26:19,203 --> 00:26:22,372
洗了十五分钟冷水澡，我才想起自己的名字。
Fifteen minutes under a cold shower before I could remember my name.

382
00:26:22,498 --> 00:26:25,417
-你听说乔·阿克曼的事了吗?——没有。什么?
- Did you hear about Joe Ackerman? - No. What?

383
00:26:25,542 --> 00:26:26,752
癌症。
Cancer.

384
00:26:26,877 --> 00:26:31,507
哦，可怜的乔，可怜的玛莎。我昨天才看到他们。
Oh, poor Joe, poor Martha. I saw them only yesterday.

385
00:26:31,632 --> 00:26:33,383
我今晚得给那里打个电话。
I'll have to call there tonight.

386
00:26:33,509 --> 00:26:35,677
那件长袍真漂亮。你从哪儿弄来的?
That's a wonderful robe. Where'd you get it?

387
00:26:35,803 --> 00:26:38,138
我想是尼克·卡罗吧。
Oh, Nick carroll's, I think.

388
00:26:39,223 --> 00:26:42,434
这是一种快乐，感觉紧挨着你的皮肤。
That's a pleasure to feel next to your skin.

389
00:26:42,559 --> 00:26:45,020
-斯迈利，你给我找几个。——会做。
- Smiley, you find me a few of those. - Will do.

390
00:26:45,145 --> 00:26:50,651
查尔斯，请您赏光参加今天下午的赛马。
Charles, we request the pleasure of your company at the races this afternoon.

391
00:26:52,069 --> 00:26:54,613
我觉得我去不了了，斯坦利。
I don't think I can make it, Stanley.

392
00:26:54,738 --> 00:26:57,199
工会规定允许的话，我可以当调酒师了。
I'm ready to bartend, union regulations permitting.

393
00:26:57,324 --> 00:26:58,659
斯坦利?
Stanley?

394
00:26:58,784 --> 00:27:01,161
给我来点苏打水，笑眯眯的。
I'll have a little sparkling water, please, smiley.

395
00:27:01,286 --> 00:27:02,955
别当老古董了，查理。
Don't be an old fossil, Charlie.

396
00:27:03,080 --> 00:27:05,391
你将享受这个下午，我们将感谢你的陪伴。
You'd enjoy the afternoon, and we'd appreciate your company.

397
00:27:05,415 --> 00:27:15,050
我很想，我真的很想，斯坦利，但事实是，一些外地的朋友，马里昂的朋友…你知道查理的为人，总是无私奉献。
I'd like to, I really would, Stanley, but the fact is, some friends from out of town, friends of Marion... You know how Charlie is, always giving of himself.

398
00:27:15,175 --> 00:27:18,387
玛丽恩，她是个好女孩。
Marion, she's a wonderful girl.

399
00:27:19,263 --> 00:27:23,517
我希望你们能和她和好，就像你们是我的家人一样。
I hope for your reconciliation with her as if you both were my own family.

400
00:27:23,642 --> 00:27:25,102
非常感谢。
Thank you very much.

401
00:27:26,186 --> 00:27:35,154
如果我们能表达神圣的意志，而幸福的婚姻肯定就是这样一种表达，那么我们就真正开始超越我们自己的自私目标了。
If we can express the divine will, and a happy marriage is certainly such an expression, then we are really beginning to live beyond our own selfish aims.

402
00:27:35,279 --> 00:27:36,905
你真好，斯坦利。
That's very sweet of you, Stanley.

403
00:27:37,030 --> 00:27:40,909
既然我们在这里进行友好的秘密会谈，那合同呢?
Since we're here on a friendly conclave, how about the contract?

404
00:27:42,494 --> 00:27:46,373
-快点，它在长胡子。-嗯，我遇到麻烦了。
- Come on, now, it's growing whiskers. - Well, I'm having trouble with it.

405
00:27:46,498 --> 00:27:50,627
麻烦吗?什么样的麻烦?你告诉我，我有宽阔的肩膀。
Trouble? What sort of trouble? You tell me, I've got broad shoulders.

406
00:27:50,752 --> 00:27:53,797
查理，人们可以对我直言不讳。
Charlie, people can speak frankly to me.

407
00:27:53,922 --> 00:27:58,844
你所处的位置使你有资格提出最高的要求，所以，请告诉我你内心深处的想法。
You're in a position which entitles you to make the highest demands, so, please, tell me your innermost thoughts.

408
00:27:58,969 --> 00:28:01,555
我不想签合同。
I don't want to sign the contract.

409
00:28:03,015 --> 00:28:06,226
-你和玛丽安谈过了吗?——是的。
- Have you talked this over with Marion? - Yes.

410
00:28:15,527 --> 00:28:19,740
你们还是夫妻啊。树和树皮。
Well, you're still man and wife. Tree and bark.

411
00:28:19,865 --> 00:28:22,784
这是上帝安排的，我能理解。
God's put that together, I can understand that.

412
00:28:23,785 --> 00:28:26,747
马里昂想在合同里看到什么?
What does Marion want to see in the contract?

413
00:28:26,872 --> 00:28:29,333
嗯,这……这是'tjust马里昂。
Well, it... it isn'tjust Marion.

414
00:28:30,626 --> 00:28:32,377
我们商量过了。
We talked it over.

415
00:28:34,546 --> 00:28:36,715
我不想再签了。
I don't want to sign again.

416
00:28:36,840 --> 00:28:40,761
-斯坦利，查理觉得…——不,不。你让他回答。
- Stanley, Charlie feels... - No, no. You let him answer.

417
00:28:42,137 --> 00:28:44,723
——为什么?-这就是全部，斯坦利
- Why? - Well, it's the whole thing, Stanley.

418
00:28:44,848 --> 00:28:49,228
签这么长时间的合同。
The whole idea of signing for that length of time.

419
00:28:49,353 --> 00:28:54,775
斯坦利，人们总是可以对你坦诚相待，而这正是查理想要做的。
Stanley, people can always speak frankly with you, and that's exactly what Charlie wants to do.

420
00:28:54,900 --> 00:29:00,739
查理……你建议怎么做呢?
Charlie... What do you propose to do instead?

421
00:29:00,864 --> 00:29:03,492
我想离开好莱坞。
Well, I want to leave Hollywood.

422
00:29:03,617 --> 00:29:08,288
我可以签任何东西保证我再也不拍电影了。
I'll sign anything guaranteeing you I'll never make pictures again.

423
00:29:08,413 --> 00:29:16,255
我对你和霍夫联邦政府没什么意见。只是……我累了。我想离开。
I've got nothing against you or hoff-federated. It's just that... I'm tired. I want to go away.

424
00:29:16,380 --> 00:29:20,300
当然,当然。我明白了。
Sure, sure. I understand.

425
00:29:23,262 --> 00:29:28,225
这样吧，你被解雇了。六个月，甚至一年。
I'll tell you what, you go on a layoff. Six months, a year even.

426
00:29:28,350 --> 00:29:30,519
不，我想永远离开。
No, I want to go for good.

427
00:29:35,524 --> 00:29:37,109
啊哦……
Uh-oh...

428
00:29:39,152 --> 00:29:40,737
我明白了。
I see.

429
00:29:40,862 --> 00:29:46,868
查理·卡塞尔，我很容易想起我们多年前的第一次见面。
Charlie castle, I easily recall to mind our first meeting many, many years ago.

430
00:29:46,994 --> 00:29:48,954
你还记得我当时说的话吗?
You remember what I said at that time?

431
00:29:49,079 --> 00:29:51,123
是的，有些东西。
Yes, some of the things.

432
00:29:51,248 --> 00:29:56,712
请原谅我闭着眼睛说话但这样能让我看得更清楚。
Please, you'll excuse me for speaking with my eyes closed but it helps me see better.

433
