"Red neon lights and a sky full of drunken blackbirds."

577
00:44:23,077 --> 00:44:25,329
这事让我很着急。
This quuor's got me in a hurry.

578
00:44:28,416 --> 00:44:30,751
不要反抗，亲爱的。
Don't fight it, darling.

579
00:44:32,461 --> 00:44:34,547
得到。
Get with it.

580
00:44:47,560 --> 00:44:48,978
喂?
Hello?

581
00:45:01,073 --> 00:45:02,909
天，我不知道，伙计。
Gee, I don't know, buddy.

582
00:45:03,743 --> 00:45:06,120
你为什么认为她会在这里?
What makes you think that she'd be here?

583
00:45:10,249 --> 00:45:11,709
现在还早。
It's early yet.

584
00:45:12,501 --> 00:45:16,339
她可能在某个商店挥霍你的战利品。
She could be out in a store somewhere squandering your loot.

585
00:45:19,675 --> 00:45:22,261
别光坐在屋子里，伙计。
Don't just sit in the house, ace.

586
00:45:23,054 --> 00:45:25,848
出去，找个酒吧，加点调味汁。
Get out, find yourself a bar, sauce up.

587
00:45:27,308 --> 00:45:28,559
确定。
Sure.

588
00:45:29,644 --> 00:45:33,231
这是卡塞尔医生随时给蓝脾气的人开的处方。
That's Dr. Castle's prescription for the blue grumps anytime.

589
00:45:37,485 --> 00:45:39,946
不,等等,老兄。不，你不能来这里。
No, wait, buddy. No, you can't come here.

590
00:45:40,071 --> 00:45:44,075
我两分钟后就要出去了。我要见一个人。
I'm going out in about two minutes. I gotta see a fellow.

591
00:45:49,622 --> 00:45:54,961
听着，我一挂电话，她可能就会进来，我现在就挂。
Look, she'll probably walk in as soon as I hang up, which is going to be right now.

592
00:45:56,170 --> 00:45:58,005
不，别谢我，伙计。
No, don't thank me, buddy.

593
00:45:59,423 --> 00:46:00,883
是的,我知道。
Yeah, I know.

594
00:46:01,717 --> 00:46:05,054
是的，我知道，我知道。我知道我是个好男人!
Oh, yes, I know, I know. I know I'm a swell guy!

595
00:46:05,179 --> 00:46:06,514
滚开!
Get out of here!

596
00:46:11,143 --> 00:46:13,312
你又伤害我了，亲爱的。
You hurt me again, darling.

597
00:46:14,397 --> 00:46:16,857
但你喜欢这样，不是吗?
But you like that, don't you?

598
00:46:19,568 --> 00:46:20,903
有个词适合你。
There's a word for you.

599
00:46:21,904 --> 00:46:25,116
为什么你不说呢，亲爱的?
Why don't you say it, darling?

600
00:46:28,411 --> 00:46:31,122
-你最好离开这里，否则我…——我知道。
- You'd better get out of here before I... - I know.

601
00:46:31,706 --> 00:46:33,124
我知道，我知道。
I know, I know.

602
00:46:33,916 --> 00:46:35,626
听着，你是什么?
Look, what are you?

603
00:46:37,878 --> 00:46:39,672
不，我是认真的。
No, I mean, seriously.

604
00:46:40,673 --> 00:46:43,342
你相信什么?什么?
Just what do you believe in? What?

605
00:46:44,593 --> 00:46:48,514
有趣，查理，不要忧郁。
Fun, Charlie, not gloomy thoughts.

606
00:46:49,932 --> 00:47:05,239
香水，青春永葆，各种各样的好东西，秘密和紧锁的门，享受进入我脑海的最狂野的事物。
Perfume and staying young, and goodies of every sort and description, and secrets and locked doors, and enjoying the wildest things that come into my mind.

607
00:47:16,792 --> 00:47:20,921
你为什么不回家，康妮?你妈妈在找你。
Why don't you go home, Connie? Your mother's looking for you.

608
00:47:22,423 --> 00:47:26,218
我要回家了，查理，一会儿就回家。
I'll go home, Charlie, in a little while.

609
00:47:26,344 --> 00:47:27,845
过一会儿。
In a little while.

610
00:47:27,970 --> 00:47:31,640
你做那个，你做那个小事情，因为我有大麻烦了。
You do that, you do that little thing, because I've got some big trouble.

611
00:47:32,183 --> 00:47:33,976
我不需要你给我添麻烦。
I don't need you for more trouble.

612
00:47:34,560 --> 00:47:38,189
我被自己的烂泥和霓虹灯弄得晕头转向。
I'm getting sloshed in my own mud and neon lights.

613
00:48:25,403 --> 00:48:27,405
——你好,马里昂。——嗨,尼克。
- Hello, Marion. - Hi, Nicky.

614
00:48:28,239 --> 00:48:31,367
没关系，但别太久。他得吃午饭。
It's all right, but don't be too long. He has to have his lunch.

615
00:48:31,909 --> 00:48:34,829
-比利，回头见。——再见。
- Billy, see you later. - Bye.

616
00:48:49,135 --> 00:48:52,012
-他感冒好了，是吧?——上周。
- He got over his cold okay, huh? - Last week.

617
00:48:53,556 --> 00:48:56,851
-我给你打了六七次电话。——我知道。
- I called you six or seven times. - I know.

618
00:48:58,853 --> 00:49:00,563
你把我埋得很深，天使。
You buried me deep, angel.

619
00:49:02,273 --> 00:49:04,024
听着，你能帮我个忙吗?
Listen, would you do me a big favor?

620
00:49:04,150 --> 00:49:05,985
——什么?-今晚来吃饭吧。
- What? - Come to dinner tonight.

621
00:49:06,569 --> 00:49:08,863
-你是说在家里?-是的。
- You mean at the house? - Yeah.

622
00:49:10,698 --> 00:49:12,825
我得为兄弟做点事。
I have to do something for buddy.

623
00:49:12,950 --> 00:49:15,411
帕蒂·本尼迪克特的事之后他就一直躲着我。
He's been avoiding me since that Patty Benedict bit.

624
00:49:15,536 --> 00:49:18,456
他觉得他让我失望了。我不知道。
He thinks he let me down or something. I don't know.

625
00:49:19,039 --> 00:49:21,208
他在前台遇到了麻烦。
He's in trouble with the front office.

626
00:49:22,001 --> 00:49:24,628
汉克邀请我今晚和他共进晚餐。
Hank asked me to have dinner with him tonight.

627
00:49:26,797 --> 00:49:28,299
好吧，把他带来。
Well, bring him along.

628
00:49:28,883 --> 00:49:33,304
-我邀请了七点钟的祝福。-好的，我们六点半到。
- I've invited the blisses for 7:00. - All right, we'll be there at 6:30.

629
00:49:36,432 --> 00:49:39,977
因为我要来家里吃晚餐，这并不意味着什么。
Because I'm coming to dinner at the house, it doesn't mean anything.

630
00:49:40,603 --> 00:49:41,896
风格。
Natch.

631
00:49:45,566 --> 00:49:47,943
“好吧，到你那边去。
'All right, into your corner.

632
00:49:48,068 --> 00:49:57,077
“三个,四个…“…5、6……“…7、8、9。
'Three, four... '...five, six... '...seven, eight, nine.

633
00:50:08,881 --> 00:50:10,132
“来吧，别闹了。
'Come on, break it up.

634
00:50:13,761 --> 00:50:14,761
分开。
'Break it up.

635
00:50:32,655 --> 00:50:34,615
“九，十，你出局了。”
'Nine, ten and you're out.'

636
00:50:56,929 --> 00:50:59,139
拍得不错，对吧，小子?
That was a great picture, huh, boy?

637
00:50:59,723 --> 00:51:02,393
嘿，查理，那家伙是谁?这是卡斯吗?
Hey, Charlie, who was that guy? Was that cass?

638
00:51:02,518 --> 00:51:04,770
是的。拉尔夫也是裁判，记住。
Yeah. Ralph was referee, too, remember.

639
00:51:04,895 --> 00:51:07,856
谁的饮料需要加糖?马里恩?康妮?
Whose drink wants sweetening? Marion? Connie?

640
00:51:08,524 --> 00:51:10,317
汉克，你为什么不停下来?
Hank, why don't you break down?

641
00:51:10,442 --> 00:51:12,820
我都快喜欢上这个了。
It's getting so I almost like this stuff.

642
00:51:12,945 --> 00:51:15,406
嘿，我们不是要去隔壁参加蒙提的派对吗?
Hey, aren't we all going next door to monty's party?

643
00:51:15,531 --> 00:51:18,325
康妮，你得原谅我。我头痛得厉害。
Connie, you'll have to excuse me. I've got a rotten headache.

644
00:51:18,450 --> 00:51:20,202
哦，真遗憾。
Oh, what a shame.

645
00:51:20,327 --> 00:51:23,330
是的，你们这些孩子快走。也许我们晚点再来找你。
Yeah, you kids run along. Maybe we'll catch up with you later.

646
00:51:23,455 --> 00:51:24,957
好的,英俊。
Okay, handsome.

647
00:51:25,583 --> 00:51:28,127
我们步行还是开车?——开车。
- Shall we walk or drive? - Drive.

648
00:51:28,252 --> 00:51:31,380
如果把车停在外面，醉鬼就会整晚都进来。
Leave a lot of cars out front, and the drunks will be dropping in all night.

649
00:51:31,505 --> 00:51:34,466
-这电影有多久了?-八九年。
- How old is that picture? - Eight, nine years.

650
00:51:34,592 --> 00:51:36,552
——为什么?-嘿，你刚才很激动。
- Why? - Hey, you had a lot of steam.

651
00:51:36,677 --> 00:51:38,178
他的确做到了。
He certainly did.

652
00:51:39,138 --> 00:51:42,224
-回见，没信仰的人-没信仰的人？
- See you later, faithless. - Faithless?

653
00:51:42,349 --> 00:51:43,851
谢谢你,查尔斯。
Thanks, Charles.

654
00:51:44,310 --> 00:51:46,478
-晚安，玛丽安。-晚安，康妮。
- Good night, Marion. - Good night, Connie.

655
00:51:47,104 --> 00:51:49,023
-晚安，汉克。——晚安。
- Good night, Hank. - Good night.

656
00:51:52,109 --> 00:51:54,111
汉克，你觉得这电影怎么样?
What did you think of the picture, Hank?

657
00:51:54,236 --> 00:51:57,364
我一直在想如果你输了那场大战会怎么样。
I kept wondering what would've happened if you lost the big fight.

658
00:51:57,489 --> 00:52:06,123
违反商业道德的。那孩子还以为他在为水星乐队和乐队写作，但结果就像霍夫叔叔说的"灾难"
Uncommercial. Kid still thinks he's writing for Mercury and the group, but it turned out to what uncle hoff described as "disaster".

659
00:52:06,290 --> 00:52:07,708
你觉得怎么样?
What did you think of it?

660
00:52:07,833 --> 00:52:10,711
我喜欢它的第一次，尽管结尾。
I liked it the first time, in spite of the ending.

661
00:52:10,836 --> 00:52:14,006
你像只哭泣的鸟儿一样哀悼过去。
Well, you grieve for the past like a weeping bird.

662
00:52:14,131 --> 00:52:15,674
汉克，你什么时候走?
When are you leaving, Hank?

663
00:52:16,675 --> 00:52:19,386
-我是说，离开好莱坞。-星期二或星期三。
- I mean, leaving Hollywood. - Tuesday or Wednesday.

664
00:52:19,511 --> 00:52:23,182
我想在你走之前见你一面。星期一怎么样?
I'd like to see you before you go. How about Monday?

665
00:52:23,307 --> 00:52:25,601
-随你便。——好吧,星期一。
- Any time you say. - Okay, Monday.

666
00:52:28,395 --> 00:52:31,398
-你在干什么?-汉克开车送我回海滩。
- What are you doing? - Hank's driving me back to the beach.

667
00:52:33,901 --> 00:52:37,780
你现在就得走吗?我是说，现在还早，12:30左右。
Do you have to go now? I mean, it's early, 12:30 or so.

668
00:52:37,905 --> 00:52:39,990
我们就不能坐下来谈谈吗?
Can't we sit down and talk or something?

669
00:52:40,115 --> 00:52:42,868
我很抱歉，查理，但你知道结果会怎样。
I'm sorry, Charlie, but you know where that leads.

670
00:52:42,993 --> 00:52:49,249
亲爱的……我想也许我们三个，我们可以坐下来聊一聊。
Darling... I thought maybe the three of us, we'd just sit around and yack it up a bit.

671
00:52:49,375 --> 00:52:50,584
请,不要走。
Please, don't go.

672
00:52:50,709 --> 00:52:53,837
听着，如果你想狂饮一番，为什么不去蒙提家?
Look, if you want to yack it up, why don't you go over to monty's?

673
00:52:53,962 --> 00:52:56,006
那里有很多聪明的人等着你。
There's lots of bright types there for you.

674
00:52:56,131 --> 00:52:57,299
别紧张，亲爱的。
Take it easy, dear.

675
00:52:57,424 --> 00:52:59,110
放轻松?这就是麻烦的开始。
Take it easy? That's where the trouble begins.

676
00:52:59,134 --> 00:53:05,057
-来吧，做你自己。-这是另一个当地的说法，意思是“像我一样，不要做你自己。”
- Come on, now, be yourself. - That's another local remark, which means, "be just like me, don't be yourself."

677
00:53:05,182 --> 00:53:09,353
-留下来再喝一杯。-我不需要了，谢谢。
- Stay and have just one more drink. - I don't need another one, thanks.

678
00:53:09,478 --> 00:53:13,440
-汉克，再来杯咖啡怎么样?-不，谢谢，查理，到这里来。
- Hank, how about another cup of coffee? - No thanks, Charlie, up to here.

679
00:53:14,191 --> 00:53:19,154
听着，有没有听过斯迈利关于咖啡豆和水草的故事?
Listen, ever hear smiley's story about the coffee bean and the water plant?

680
00:53:24,910 --> 00:53:31,291
汉克……玛丽安告诉我你向她求婚了。
Hank... Marion tells me that you asked her to marry you.

681
00:53:31,417 --> 00:53:32,584
是的,我做到了。
Yes, I did.

682
00:53:33,127 --> 00:53:34,837
让我搞清楚。
Let me get this straight.

683
00:53:34,962 --> 00:53:39,341
-你不是我的朋友吗?——是的,查理……那这个程序是什么?
- Aren't you my friend? - Yes, Charlie... Then what is this routine?

684
00:53:41,802 --> 00:53:44,221
玛丽安让我想活下去。
Marion makes me want to live.

685
00:53:44,346 --> 00:53:46,890
大多数人对我的影响是不同的。
Most people affect me differently.

686
00:53:47,015 --> 00:53:50,227
查理，我很抱歉你不开心，但你几年前就失去她了。
Look, Charlie, I'm sorry you're unhappy, but you lost her years ago.

687
00:53:50,352 --> 00:53:52,062
公平地说，你不能怪我。
In fairness, you can't blame me.

688
00:53:52,187 --> 00:53:55,065
今晚我觉得不公平。你把你的天使翅膀藏哪了?
I don't feel fair tonight. Where did you stash your angel wings?

689
00:53:55,190 --> 00:53:57,317
谁给你权利做这样的决定的?
Who gave you the right to make such a decision?

690
00:53:57,443 --> 00:54:00,112
我唯一的权利是自己做决定。
My only right is to make my own decisions.

691
00:54:00,696 --> 00:54:02,740
你的演讲就在沙发上。
That speech is right off the couch.

692
00:54:03,866 --> 00:54:06,702
说实话吧，梦中男孩。玛丽安不会离开我的。
Get this straight, dreamboy. Marion isn't going to leave me.

693
00:54:06,827 --> 00:54:08,537
我也自己做决定。
I make my own decisions, too.

694
00:54:08,662 --> 00:54:10,372
-听…-不，我想回家。
- Listen... - No, I want to go home.

695
00:54:10,497 --> 00:54:12,458
玛丽恩，你能让我说十句话吗?
Marion, would you let me say 10 words?

696
00:54:12,583 --> 00:54:15,085
我想我还是在车里等好了。
I think it'll be easier if I wait in the car.

697
00:54:30,768 --> 00:54:32,102
我很抱歉。
I'm sorry.

698
00:54:32,770 --> 00:54:36,315
有时我不停地咆哮，好像我对你有什么不满似的。
Sometimes I rant and rave as though I had something against you.

699
00:54:37,775 --> 00:54:40,277
但你一直对我很好，非常好。
But you've been good to me, so good to me.

700
00:54:41,737 --> 00:54:43,572
你只对我好。
You're only good to me.

701
00:54:50,370 --> 00:54:57,544
这一切都是一个凄凉、痛苦的梦，一盘真正的鸽子。
This is all a bleak, bitter dream, a real dish of doves.

702
00:54:59,171 --> 00:55:04,468
你跑到这儿来，把一窝光着身子的鸽子扔到我面前，我能做什么，我能说什么?
You come in here and throw this nest of naked pigeons in my face, what can I do, what can I say?

703
00:55:04,593 --> 00:55:06,154
只有两种方法可以忘记这一切。
There are only two ways to forget everything.

704
00:55:06,178 --> 00:55:09,097
你要么喝醉，要么把铅笔插进眼睛。
You either get drunk, or you just stick a pencil in your eye.

705
00:55:09,223 --> 00:55:12,518
查理，我明早要见律师。
Charlie, I'm seeing a lawyer in the morning.

706
00:55:14,561 --> 00:55:16,730
玛丽恩，求你了，不要离开我。
Marion, please, don't leave me.

707
00:55:19,608 --> 00:55:21,527
我发誓，我是无辜的，天使。
I swear, I'm innocent, angel.

708
00:55:21,652 --> 00:55:29,243
我发誓当我用我的光芒魅力世人的时候，我会在我的衬衫下面流血而死。
I swear that while I'm charming the world with my light fantastic, I'm bleeding to death under my shirt.

709
00:55:33,413 --> 00:55:35,749
你就不能和律师一起等吗，小天使?
Can't you wait with the lawyer, angel?

710
00:55:38,335 --> 00:55:40,337
我是世界上最蠢的笨蛋吗?
Am I the worst oaf in the world?

711
00:55:41,672 --> 00:55:43,298
世界这么大。
The world's a big place.

712
00:55:44,341 --> 00:55:46,760
你是我这辈子最糟糕的人。
You're the worst one in my life.

713
00:56:06,989 --> 00:56:08,407
谢谢你！
Thank you.

714
00:56:09,324 --> 00:56:11,618
要我带你回去吗?
Do want me to take you back?

715
00:56:13,871 --> 00:56:19,626
哦,汉克…玛丽安，你知道我爱你。为了你的幸福，我愿意做任何事。
Oh, Hank... Marion, you know I love you. I'll do anything for your happiness.

716
00:56:19,751 --> 00:56:22,838
但求你了，别再两头为难了。
But please, stop playing both ends against the middle.

717
00:56:22,963 --> 00:56:24,506
我不是故意的。
I don't mean to.

718
00:56:25,549 --> 00:56:28,343
那么让我们来面对基本的问题。
Then let's face the basic problem.

719
00:56:29,511 --> 00:56:31,555
这可以归结为一个简单的事实。
It boils down to a simple fact.

720
00:56:32,890 --> 00:56:39,187
要么你还爱着他，想和他生活在一起，要么你不爱他，不想和他生活在一起。
Either you still love him and you want to live with him, or you don't love him and you don't want to live with him.

721
00:56:41,273 --> 00:56:45,861
查理，求你了，别担心。一切都会好起来的。
Charlie, please, don't worry. It'll all work out.

722
00:56:47,946 --> 00:56:50,991
-尼基，帮我个忙。——当然,查理。
- Nicky, do me a favor. - Sure, Charlie.

723
00:56:52,034 --> 00:56:54,494
把我的睡袍和毯子拿来。
Get me my robe and a blanket.

724
00:56:55,954 --> 00:56:59,625
-我今晚不想睡在上面。——确定。
- I don't want to sleep up there tonight. - Sure.

725
00:57:05,172 --> 00:57:13,764
看,查理……如果你有麻烦，如果老尼克能帮上什么忙，任何事。
Look, Charlie... If you're in trouble, if there's anything old Nick can do, anything.

726
00:57:14,723 --> 00:57:17,517
有人在家吗?Nang-nang-nang !
Anybody home? Nang-nang-nang!

727
00:57:17,643 --> 00:57:20,228
我什么都没听到，什么都没听到。
I don't hear a thing, not a thing.

728
00:57:20,354 --> 00:57:23,315
你从哪里来?隔壁吗?
Where did you come from? Next door?

729
00:57:23,440 --> 00:57:26,485
是的。蒙蒂丽兹。一个真正的bash。
Yeah. Monty ritz. A real bash.

730
00:57:26,610 --> 00:57:30,197
-真有趣，你在这里听不到。-不，我把门关着的。
- Funny, you couldn't hear it in here. - No, I had the door closed.

731
00:57:32,199 --> 00:57:35,577
-听起来很疯狂。-所有的类型。你知道蒙蒂。
- It sounds wild. - All the types. You know monty.

732
00:57:35,702 --> 00:57:37,329
和女孩们一起被抓?
Busted with the girls?

733
00:57:38,080 --> 00:57:39,206
一切。
Everything.

734
00:57:40,749 --> 00:57:43,502
-你感觉怎么样，凯蒂?——蓝色。
- How you feeling, kitty? - Blue.

735
00:57:43,627 --> 00:57:45,796
就像我亲爱的宝贝的眼睛。
Like my dear baby's eyes.

736
00:57:46,672 --> 00:57:48,674
-你觉得泰丝怎么样?——苔丝?
- What did you think of Tess? - Tess?

737
00:57:49,341 --> 00:57:52,928
——昨晚。-那个红头发的。
- Last night. - Oh, the redhead.

738
00:57:53,053 --> 00:57:58,809
她是天生的，但是…我不知道，我当时没心情。我想我失去了一个粉丝。
She was built, but... I don't know, I wasn't in the mood. I think I lost a fan.

739
00:57:59,601 --> 00:58:01,436
我回到家读了一个小时的书。
I came home and read for an hour.

740
00:58:01,561 --> 00:58:03,647
你在读什么?
What are you reading?

741
00:58:03,772 --> 00:58:06,441
我不记得从哪一天到哪一天。
I don't remember from one day to another.

742
00:58:06,566 --> 00:58:09,528
我今天下午看了汤米·默多克的新电影。
I saw Tommy murdock's new picture this afternoon.

743
00:58:09,653 --> 00:58:12,948
-是啊，怎么样?——灾难。
- Yeah, how was it? - Disaster.

744
00:58:14,616 --> 00:58:18,286
打牌还是下棋，还是玩拼字游戏再收你100块?
Cards or chess, or shall I take another $100 from you at scrabble?

745
00:58:18,412 --> 00:58:20,414
不，这次我们不去了。
No, let's sit this one out.

746
00:58:21,498 --> 00:58:23,750
你在做什么梦?
What are you dreaming about?

747
00:58:23,875 --> 00:58:27,045
我想家了，想东方的四季。
I'm homesick for the east, the four seasons.

748
00:58:29,006 --> 00:58:32,092
-你多大了，smiley?-一百万。
- How old are you, smiley? - A million.

749
00:58:33,635 --> 00:58:39,182
但令我惊讶的是，我还这么年轻，居然还对迪克西·埃文斯这样的流浪汉发脾气。
But young enough, to my surprise, to still be losing my temper with a tramp like Dixie Evans.

750
00:58:41,476 --> 00:58:44,312
-又怎么了?-她的嘴太大了。
- What's wrong now? - Her mouth's too big.

751
00:58:45,856 --> 00:58:49,526
她在蒙蒂的派对上，喝醉了。“他在那儿，”她说。
She's over at monty's party, drunk. "There he is," she says.

752
00:58:49,651 --> 00:58:54,281
我转过身，看到她坐在那里，可爱得像剥了皮的半熟火腿。
I turn around, and there she sits, cute as a skinned parboiled ham.

753
00:58:54,406 --> 00:58:58,160
“我们知道一些事情，smiley和我，不是吗?”她说。
"We know something, smiley and me, don't we?" She says.

754
00:58:58,285 --> 00:59:00,620
我一直想让玛丽安回到我身边。
I've been trying to get Marion to come back to me.

755
00:59:00,746 --> 00:59:02,205
——是吗?-是的。
- Yeah? - Yeah.

756
00:59:02,330 --> 00:59:06,501
我只需要这些，就能让她发现车祸那晚我车里有个女孩。
That's all I need, for her to find out I had a girl in the car the night of the accident.

757
00:59:06,626 --> 00:59:09,171
迪克西在很多地方都有这样的暗示。
Dixie's been hinting like that in quite a few spots.

758
00:59:09,296 --> 00:59:12,966
-你觉得她有恶意吗?-谁知道什么是伤害?
- You think she means any harm? - Who knows harm?

759
00:59:13,592 --> 00:59:15,886
她一直都很喜欢你，凯蒂。
She's always liked you, kitty.

760
00:59:16,011 --> 00:59:17,864
打电话给她，让她过来。笑一点。
Call her up, have her come over. Laugh a little.

761
00:59:17,888 --> 00:59:22,684
你担心吗?你在担心什么?你可以做上千件事。
You're worried? What are you worried about? You can do a thousand things.

762
00:59:22,809 --> 00:59:23,977
一个名字。
Name one.

763
00:59:24,102 --> 00:59:26,813
-收买她。-我们签了合同。
- Buy her off. - We did, with a contract.

764
00:59:26,938 --> 00:59:29,733
哦,是的。她是不诚实的。她不会被收买的。
Oh, yes. She's dishonest. She won't stay bought.

765
00:59:30,984 --> 00:59:34,571
-叫她过来，凯蒂。——好的。
- Call her over, kitty. - All right.

766
00:59:37,657 --> 00:59:39,951
为了我的艺术，什么都可以。
Anything for my art.

767
00:59:42,204 --> 00:59:44,581
女人,女人,女人。
Women, women, women.

768
00:59:44,706 --> 00:59:47,084
是蒙提的小女孩在唱歌。
It's monty's little girl singing.

769
00:59:47,209 --> 00:59:49,044
好声音。
Nice voice.

770
00:59:49,169 --> 00:59:50,962
你应该看看她。
You should see her.

771
00:59:51,088 --> 00:59:53,507
——可爱,嗯?——梭鱼。
- Cute, huh? - A barracuda.

772
00:59:54,966 --> 00:59:59,221
喂?迪克西·埃文斯小姐在吗?
Hello? Miss Dixie Evans is there?

773
01:00:00,931 --> 01:00:04,601
埃文斯。是的。请接她好吗?
Evans. Yes. Would you get her, please?

774
01:00:06,228 --> 01:00:08,855
听起来像是在开枪什么的。
Sounds like they're shooting off guns or something.

775
01:00:08,980 --> 01:00:10,482
羚羊的一种。
Bongos.

776
01:00:11,566 --> 01:00:14,069
-那里有很多女人?——加载。
- A lot of women there? - Loaded.

777
01:00:15,320 --> 01:00:17,864
凯蒂，你觉得女人怎么样?
What do you think of women, kitty?

778
01:00:18,824 --> 01:00:21,868
世界上有他们的一席之地。
There's room in the world for them.

779
01:00:21,993 --> 01:00:23,453
迪克西?
Dixie?

780
01:00:24,955 --> 01:00:27,165
我听不见你说什么。谁?
I can't hear you. Who?

781
01:00:30,961 --> 01:00:34,756
真的吗?你不是在开玩笑吧?
Really? You're not ribbing me?

782
01:00:35,257 --> 01:00:37,050
别闹了，好吗，亲爱的?
Knock it off, will you, honey?

783
01:00:37,175 --> 01:00:40,387
不，不是你，查理。有人和我在一起。
No, not you, Charlie. There's somebody here with me.

784
01:00:40,512 --> 01:00:43,473
当然，这是一个很棒的聚会。你在哪里?
Sure, it's a great party. Where are you?

785
01:00:44,057 --> 01:00:46,017
这里太吵了。
There's so much noise here.

786
01:00:46,143 --> 01:00:48,436
-你能让他停下来吗?-没事的。
- Would you please get him to stop? - It's all right.

787
01:00:48,562 --> 01:00:51,415
-不，我有个很重要的电话。-没事的，宝贝，他会安静的。
- No, I have a very important call. - It's all right, honey, he'll be quiet.

788
01:00:51,439 --> 01:00:56,319
喂?查理，在你的泳池里游泳?
Hello? Gee, Charlie, a swim in your pool now?

789
01:00:56,444 --> 01:00:57,946
我很乐意。
Well, I'd love to.

790
01:00:58,071 --> 01:01:00,031
听着，我怎么去那里?
Listen, how do I get there?

791
01:01:00,157 --> 01:01:01,199
是吗?
Yeah?

792
01:01:01,324 --> 01:01:03,994
听着，你能别闹了吗，亲爱的?
Look, will you cut it out, please, honey?

793
01:01:04,119 --> 01:01:05,370
嗯?
Huh?

794
01:01:06,163 --> 01:01:08,248
听着，我要蒙蒂的车。
Look, I'll take monty's car.

795
01:01:08,373 --> 01:01:10,876
是啊，你知道我从不走路。
Yeah, you know I never walk anywhere.

796
01:01:11,001 --> 01:01:14,171
是的,马上。医师。我很乐意!
Yeah, right away. Pronto. I'd love to!

797
01:01:14,296 --> 01:01:17,048
哦，在所有的类型中!
Oh, of all the types!

798
01:01:18,842 --> 01:01:22,637
这是我一个月来遇到的第一件好事。
The first nice thing that's happened to me in a month of Tuesdays.

799
01:01:27,559 --> 01:01:28,643
再见,亲爱的。
Bye, honey.

800
01:01:28,768 --> 01:01:33,773
小心你对迪克西说的话，查理。别再给她口实了。
Careful what you say to Dixie, Charlie. Don't give her any more ammunition.

801
01:01:33,899 --> 01:01:36,067
听着，你有没有提出买断她的合同?
Listen, have you offered to buy her contract up?

802
01:01:36,193 --> 01:01:39,821
-两个月前。什么都没有。——两个月?
- Two months ago. Nothing. - Two months?

803
01:01:39,946 --> 01:01:42,157
你是说，她泄密这么久了?
You mean, she's been blabbing that long?

804
01:01:42,282 --> 01:01:47,495
朗根这个愚蠢的小流浪汉。只有一点点力量的两个零。
Longen the stupid little tramp. Two bits worth of nothing with a little power.

805
01:01:47,621 --> 01:01:51,458
-她不想要更多的钱?-她不知道自己想要什么。
- She doesn't want more money? - She doesn't know what she wants.

806
01:01:51,583 --> 01:01:53,793
我敢打赌，我们得除掉她。
I'm betting even money, we have to get rid of her.

807
01:01:53,919 --> 01:01:55,587
很好。你是怎么做到的?
Fine. How do you work that?

808
01:02:09,601 --> 01:02:11,811
——晚安,查理。——晚安。
- Goodnight, Charlie. - Goodnight.

809
01:02:15,774 --> 01:02:18,193
你是怎么做到的?
How do you work that?

810
01:02:18,318 --> 01:02:20,362
没有标准的程序。
There's no standard procedure.

811
01:02:20,487 --> 01:02:22,489
你是做什么的，把她往东运吗?
What do you do, ship her east?

812
01:02:22,614 --> 01:02:26,409
查理，她一张嘴就说个不停。
Charlie, she's all mouth, all gab.

813
01:02:26,534 --> 01:02:30,080
所以我们得把它修好她再也不能张嘴了。
So we've got to get it fixed she never opens her mouth again.

814
01:02:30,872 --> 01:02:33,583
那我们就等着看事态的发展吧。
Well, let's wait and see the developments.

815
01:02:33,708 --> 01:02:36,294
我想我能和她谈谈。
I think I can talk to her.

816
01:02:41,925 --> 01:02:43,301
我今晚有点迷糊。
I'm a little fuzzy tonight.

817
01:02:43,426 --> 01:02:47,681
你说的话很有趣，笑眯眯的，但我没看到你笑。
You're saying funny things, smiley, but I don't see you smiling.

818
01:02:47,806 --> 01:02:50,809
你说"她再也不开口"是什么意思
What do you mean, "she never opens her mouth again?"

819
01:02:50,934 --> 01:02:53,353
——就是这样。——什么?
- That's it. - What's it?

820
01:02:54,729 --> 01:02:57,983
查理，她必须被移走。
Charlie, she'll have to be removed.

821
01:02:58,108 --> 01:02:59,985
删除吗?
Removed?

822
01:03:00,110 --> 01:03:02,445
抱歉把生肉扔到地上了。
Sorry to throw the raw meat on the floor.

823
01:03:02,570 --> 01:03:06,950
事实就像岩石一样，有一定的尺寸和重力。
A fact, like a rock, has certain dimensions and gravity.

824
01:03:07,075 --> 01:03:09,577
我把所有的选项一个一个看了一遍。
I've gone over all the choices, one by one.

825
01:03:11,621 --> 01:03:13,456
你会成为一个很棒的演员。
You'd make a great actor.

826
01:03:14,416 --> 01:03:17,711
-生活就是个奇怪的小人，凯蒂。——是的,基蒂。
- Life's a queer little man, kitty. - Yeah, kitty.

827
01:03:19,129 --> 01:03:22,632
-史丹利知道些什么?-只知道他想知道的。
- What does Stanley know about this? - Only what he wants to know.

828
01:03:22,757 --> 01:03:26,219
他每年付给我七万五千英镑是有原因的，凯蒂。
There's a reason he pays me £75,000 a year, kitty.

829
01:03:29,347 --> 01:03:33,977
-有那么一分钟，我想…-查理，你是个爱幻想的人。
- For a minute there, I thought... - Charlie, you're a fanciful type.

830
01:03:34,102 --> 01:03:37,522
在我这行，你得了解类型。把你的类型。
In my end of the business, you have to know types. Take your type.

831
01:03:37,647 --> 01:03:40,984
怀着渺茫希望的武士吟游诗人。
The warrior minstrel with a forlorn hope.

832
01:03:42,319 --> 01:03:44,529
这是你,娃娃。
That's you, doll.

833
01:03:44,654 --> 01:03:46,614
这是南方。我从后门溜出去。
That's Dixie. I'll slide out the back way.

834
01:03:46,740 --> 01:03:49,784
"抱着渺茫希望的武士吟游诗人"等待。
"Warrior minstrel with the forlorn hope." Wait.

835
01:03:49,909 --> 01:03:51,578
那是什么?
What's that from?

836
01:03:51,703 --> 01:03:53,747
这是爱尔兰人常说的一句话。
It's a phrase the Irish used to understand.

837
01:03:53,872 --> 01:03:57,709
你了解我的，我来自那些愤世嫉俗的凯尔特人。
You know me, I'm from those cynical celts.

838
01:03:57,834 --> 01:03:59,961
理想,基蒂?现在吗?
Ideals, kitty? Nowadays?

839
01:04:01,796 --> 01:04:03,840
一个失落的十字军东征。
A lost crusade.

840
01:04:04,841 --> 01:04:07,886
不要研究生活，查理。要习惯它。
Don't study life, Charlie. Get used to it.

841
01:04:08,011 --> 01:04:10,638
嘿，你转移话题了。
Hey, you changed the subject.

842
01:04:10,764 --> 01:04:13,683
你想记住我今晚说的一切吗?
You bothering to remember everything I said tonight?

843
01:04:14,267 --> 01:04:15,852
祝你有个好梦,基蒂。
Pleasant dreams, kitty.

844
01:04:19,939 --> 01:04:21,232
微笑,听着。
Smiley, listen.

845
01:04:23,318 --> 01:04:24,736
查理?
Charlie?

846
01:04:28,448 --> 01:04:29,949
查理?
Charlie?

847
01:04:33,453 --> 01:04:36,039
门没锁，所以我直接走了进去。
The door wasn't locked, so I walked right in.

848
01:04:36,164 --> 01:04:38,458
好久不见了，查理。
Long time, no see, Charlie.

849
01:04:38,666 --> 01:04:41,169
那就用威士忌漱口吧。
Well, wash my mouth out with whiskey.

850
01:04:53,306 --> 01:04:55,225
我正在喝白兰地。
I'm drinking Brandy.

851
01:04:55,350 --> 01:04:58,686
如果我再喝一杯，就会看到一条蛇。
If I take one more drink, I'll see a snake.

852
01:05:04,692 --> 01:05:06,861
拿一个轻的。别傻了。
Take a light one. Don't be silly.

853
01:05:06,986 --> 01:05:09,823
好吧，你这个受虐狂。
All right, you masochist.

854
01:05:11,491 --> 01:05:13,451
给我一杯加苏打水的苏格兰威士忌。
Give me a scotch and soda.

855
01:05:13,576 --> 01:05:14,911
我知道。
I know.

856
01:05:20,500 --> 01:05:22,919
你怎么知道我参加了蒙蒂的派对?
How did you know I was at monty's party?

857
01:05:26,089 --> 01:05:27,632
哦，你是个骗子。
Oh, you're a faker.

858
01:05:27,757 --> 01:05:30,260
你人很好，但我不信任你。
You're very sweet, but I don't trust you.

859
01:05:32,095 --> 01:05:36,266
听……-谁在家?-只有蟋蟀。
Listen... - Who's at home? - Only the crickets.

860
01:05:37,642 --> 01:05:43,022
查理……-你为什么不再喜欢我了?-我喜欢你，迪克西
Charlie... - Why don't you like me anymore? - I like you, Dixie.

861
01:05:43,148 --> 01:05:49,237
自从那天我和你还有你的探员坐在这张椅子上之后就再没见过你了。
Oh, I haven't seen you since that very day I sat in this here chair with you and your agents.

862
01:05:49,362 --> 01:05:52,824
当我问他们要合同的时候，他们很震惊。
Then I shocked them when I asked for my contract.

863
01:05:52,949 --> 01:05:54,993
亲爱的，老纳特是老手了。
Old nat's been around, honey.

864
01:05:55,118 --> 01:06:00,331
整个大工作室，当我想到他们做的和说的一些事情。
And that whole big studio, when I think of some of the things they do and say.

865
01:06:00,457 --> 01:06:02,041
如?
Such as?

866
01:06:03,376 --> 01:06:06,504
只有身材好的女孩才会知道。
You've got to be a girl with a good figure to know.

867
01:06:07,172 --> 01:06:10,508
还有一些人在雨天的下午。
And some of those guys on a rainy afternoon.

868
01:06:10,633 --> 01:06:12,802
我真想把他们的脑袋给砸了。
I'd like to brain 'em.

869
01:06:15,138 --> 01:06:18,433
你知道我身材很匀称吗?
Did you know that I'm perfectly proportioned?

870
01:06:18,558 --> 01:06:20,268
-不是吗?——是的。
- Well, aren't I? - Yes.

871
01:06:20,393 --> 01:06:25,398
当然，我现在明白了气质比体型和大小重要得多。
Of course, I understand now that temperament is much more important than shape and size.

872
01:06:25,523 --> 01:06:27,692
但我还是不愿意戴眼镜。
But it's like I still won't get glasses.

873
01:06:27,817 --> 01:06:31,446
你知道，我看不见街对面。但是眼镜很丑，不是吗?
You know, I can't see across the street. But glasses are ugly, aren't they?

874
01:06:31,571 --> 01:06:33,239
谁惹我生气了?
Who wound me up?

875
01:06:33,364 --> 01:06:34,782
到这里来。
Come here.

876
01:06:36,159 --> 01:06:39,329
那为什么在我年轻激动人心的生活中，我很少见到你呢?
So why don't I see you more often in my young and thrilling life?

877
01:06:39,454 --> 01:06:42,540
给，来一针卡塞尔医生的止痛药。
Here, have a shot of Dr. Castle's pain killer.

878
01:06:43,625 --> 01:06:45,168
蛇油。
Snake oil.

879
01:06:47,170 --> 01:06:49,130
我才不管有没有看到蛇。
I don't care if I do see a snake.

880
01:06:50,215 --> 01:06:53,426
我肯定我更愿意看到一条蛇，而不是一个好莱坞制片人。
I'm sure I'd much rather see a snake than a Hollywood producer.

881
01:06:55,553 --> 01:06:58,306
谁发明了苏打水?他们是怎么做的?
Who invented soda? How do they make it?

882
01:06:58,431 --> 01:07:00,308
哦，真是个怪人!
Ooh, what a weirdie!

883
01:07:00,975 --> 01:07:03,353
你是唯一一个这么叫我的人。
You're the only one who can call me that.

884
01:07:03,478 --> 01:07:05,230
我来告诉你为什么。
I'll tell you why.

885
01:07:05,355 --> 01:07:07,023
我喜欢你，查理。
I like you, Charlie.

886
01:07:07,941 --> 01:07:10,777
你一直对我很好，很体贴。
You've been very kind and considerate to me.

887
01:07:10,902 --> 01:07:14,781
这是我特殊记忆盒里的一件非常特别的事。
And that is a very special matter in my special memory box.

888
01:07:17,951 --> 01:07:21,412
我打算养只狗。贵宾犬。
I'm going to get a dog. A poodle.

889
01:07:23,081 --> 01:07:26,251
你喜欢狮子狗吗?大的还是小的?
- Do you like poodles? - Big or little?

890
01:07:26,376 --> 01:07:28,253
我来告诉你为什么。
I'll tell you why.

891
01:07:29,587 --> 01:07:33,091
我16岁的时候，我的家人把我赶出了家门。
When I was 16, my family threw me out of the house.

892
01:07:33,216 --> 01:07:35,093
这让你非常紧张。
That makes you very nervous.

893
01:07:35,218 --> 01:07:38,263
我是说，这种事让你很敏感。
I mean, a thing like that makes you very touchy.

894
01:07:39,222 --> 01:07:41,391
他们只是觉得我输了。
They just kind of gave me up for lost.

895
01:07:43,268 --> 01:07:48,398
直到今天，我母亲还不能告诉父亲我给他们寄钱。
To this very day, my mother can't tell my father that I send them money.

896
01:07:48,523 --> 01:07:50,984
天主教徒信奉大家庭。
Catholics believe in large families.

897
01:07:51,776 --> 01:07:54,487
但我告诉你，我现在正在存钱。
But I'll tell you what, I'm saving my money now.

898
01:07:54,612 --> 01:07:57,365
我在等待白马王子的到来。
I'm waiting for Mr. Right to come along.

899
01:07:57,490 --> 01:07:59,576
如果我在这附近遇到他。
If I ever meet the guy around here.

900
01:08:00,660 --> 01:08:03,246
我在好莱坞名声扫地。
My name is mud in Hollywood.

901
01:08:04,080 --> 01:08:07,417
-嘿，我烦你了吗?-不，亲爱的，不。
- Hey, am I boring you? - No, honey, no.

902
01:08:08,334 --> 01:08:10,253
我喜欢听你说实话。
I like to hear you talk honest.

903
01:08:11,296 --> 01:08:13,798
我知道你想干什么，查理。
I know what you're trying to do, Charlie.

904
01:08:13,923 --> 01:08:15,133
什么?
What?

905
01:08:15,883 --> 01:08:19,345
让我忘记你答应过我的游泳。
Make me forget about the swim you promised me.

906
01:08:19,470 --> 01:08:22,432
如果可以的话，他们会淹死我的，那个工作室。
They'd drown me if they could, that studio.

907
01:08:23,224 --> 01:08:24,434
为什么?
Why?

908
01:08:25,852 --> 01:08:27,604
我针。
I needle them.

909
01:08:27,729 --> 01:08:31,941
我一直在暗示你的事故。这让他们对改变感到紧张。
I keep hinting about your accident. It makes them nervous for a change.

910
01:08:32,066 --> 01:08:36,487
你要小心。霍夫是个鳄鱼脾气的人。
You want to be careful. Hoff's a man with a crocodile's temper.

911
01:08:37,864 --> 01:08:40,742
别跟我说霍夫先生。
Don't tell me about Mr. Hoff.

912
01:08:40,867 --> 01:08:44,912
前一分钟还叫我孩子，甚至连脸都没变……
Calling me a child one minute, and without even changing his face...

913
01:08:47,123 --> 01:08:51,002
你不像我那样从底层看待这些人，查理。
You don't see those people from the bottom like I do, Charlie.

914
01:08:51,127 --> 01:08:58,343
-你是一个白手起家的成功人士。-迪克西…饶了我吧，拜托了?
- You're a successful self-made man. - Dixie... Why don't you give me a break, please?

915
01:08:58,468 --> 01:09:00,511
当然,查理,亲爱的。如何?
Sure, Charlie, dear. How?

916
01:09:00,637 --> 01:09:07,226
每次你说起那次事故，你知道的…哦，查理，别这样!
Well, every time that you talk about the accident, you know... Oh, Charlie, don't be like that!

917
01:09:07,352 --> 01:09:10,063
你不用怕我。
You have nothing to be afraid of from me.

918
01:09:10,188 --> 01:09:11,898
我不会说梦话的。
I don't talk in my sleep.

919
01:09:13,441 --> 01:09:16,277
-所以别担心。-但我很担心，小酒窝。
- So don't worry. - But I am worried, dimples.

920
01:09:16,402 --> 01:09:23,534
某天晚上，你会在不经意间喝得大醉……但我现在已经喝得酩酊大醉了，而且我还没告诉你你不知道的事，对吧?
Some night, you'll have a skinful and inadvertently... But I've got a skinful now, and I didn't tell you anything you didn't know already, did I?

921
01:09:23,660 --> 01:09:28,873
比如萨米·伯克。他带走了这个女孩…迪克西!
Like about Sammy Burke for instance. Now, he took this girl... Dixie!

922
01:09:31,751 --> 01:09:33,294
你现在才告诉我。
You're telling me now.

923
01:09:35,004 --> 01:09:37,757
那是因为你问我的。
That's because you asked me.

924
01:09:38,675 --> 01:09:40,134
不，我没问你。
No, I didn't ask you.

925
01:09:41,969 --> 01:09:47,475
我只是举个例子。查理，亲爱的，我知道该停在哪里。
I'm only giving you an example. Charlie, dear, I know where to stop.

926
01:09:47,600 --> 01:09:50,895
但我看不出有什么理由让他们好过。
But I don't see any reason to make it easy on them.

927
01:09:52,105 --> 01:09:53,856
我讨厌他们。
I hate them.

928
01:09:53,981 --> 01:09:58,695
我的合同上写着"演员"但他们雇我是为了我的身材，不是为了演戏。
You know, it says "actress" on my contract, but they hired me for my figure, not to act.

929
01:09:58,820 --> 01:10:01,823
-但你一直在演戏。——那些部分?
- But you've been acting. - Those bits?

930
01:10:01,948 --> 01:10:06,035
两年内有三个抽香烟的女孩。这叫演戏吗?
Three cigarette girls in two whole years. You call that acting?

931
01:10:06,953 --> 01:10:09,956
“接下来是重要的部分。下周测试你们。
"Big part coming up. Testing you next week.

932
01:10:10,081 --> 01:10:12,417
“你不出来吃饭吗?”
"Won't you come out to dinner?"

933
01:10:12,542 --> 01:10:14,544
下周永远不会到来。
And next week never comes.

934
01:10:15,670 --> 01:10:20,216
查理，他们雇像我这样的女孩来招待来访的参展商。
Charlie, they hire girls like me to entertain the visiting exhibitors.

935
01:10:20,341 --> 01:10:23,052
我们会跳舞，会穿衣服。
We know how to dance and dress.

936
01:10:23,177 --> 01:10:25,513
衣服从衣柜里出来了。
The clothes come out of wardrobe.

937
01:10:25,638 --> 01:10:27,598
这比他们…
It's cheaper than if they...

938
01:10:29,809 --> 01:10:34,313
我是免赔项目。他们把我排除在外了!
I'm a deductible item. They write me off the books!

939
01:10:34,439 --> 01:10:38,860
听我叔叔的话，柯利牧羊犬。你为什么不回去…那糟糕的工作室!
Listen to uncle, collie dog. Why don't you go back... That lousy studio!

940
01:10:38,985 --> 01:10:42,280
他们把你弄得一团糟，然后叫你虱子!
They louse you up, and then they call you a louse!

941
01:10:48,745 --> 01:10:50,747
诚实,查理……
Honest, Charlie...

942
01:10:52,999 --> 01:10:55,376
你不会生气吗?
Wouldn't you be mad?

943
01:10:56,502 --> 01:10:58,171
当然我会的。
Sure I would.

944
01:10:59,589 --> 01:11:01,883
嗯,那里。看到了吗?
Well, there. See?

945
01:11:09,682 --> 01:11:13,019
看看这个。这是我学到的。
Look at this bit. It's what I learned.

946
01:11:15,021 --> 01:11:19,942
可爱的小宝贝……你答应过我的游泳池在哪儿?
Dearie... Where is zis swimming pool you promised me?

947
01:11:21,194 --> 01:11:23,362
在这里。来了。
Here. Coming right up.

948
01:11:23,488 --> 01:11:25,573
充满了白兰地。
Filled with Brandy.

949
01:11:25,698 --> 01:11:30,745
因为孩子，不能让她久等。哦!
Because the baby, she cannot be kept waiting. Oh!

950
01:11:34,040 --> 01:11:36,959
有人站在那儿吗?
Hey, is there somebody standing there?

951
01:11:50,515 --> 01:11:52,350
这是我的妻子。
This is my wife.

952
01:11:53,935 --> 01:11:55,311
埃文斯小姐。
Miss Evans.

953
01:11:55,436 --> 01:11:58,105
呃…很高兴见到你，卡塞尔夫人。
Er... pleased to meet you, Mrs. Castle.

954
01:12:00,942 --> 01:12:03,778
呃…我们在聊天。
Er... we were having a conversation.

955
01:12:04,862 --> 01:12:07,990
我得回去参加蒙提的派对了，查理。
Well, I've got to get back to monty's party now, Charlie.

956
01:12:08,866 --> 01:12:12,411
谢谢你的酒和对我事业的建议。
Thanks for the drink and the advice about my career.

957
01:12:12,537 --> 01:12:15,331
当然,迪克西。谢谢你过来。
Sure, Dixie. Thanks for coming over.

958
01:12:19,210 --> 01:12:21,128
非常愉快。
It's been very pleasant.

959
01:12:22,171 --> 01:12:26,592
但是，查理，我说的关于工作室的话都是认真的。
But, Charlie, I meant everything I said about the studio.

960
01:12:28,344 --> 01:12:30,263
晚安,Castle夫人
Goodnight, Mrs. Castle.

961
01:12:32,849 --> 01:12:35,977
还好我没在游泳池里发现亚当和夏娃。
Lucky I didn't find Adam and Eve in the swimming pool.

962
01:12:36,102 --> 01:12:39,689
-你错了，她有点…-我不管她是什么。
- You're wrong, she's a little... - I don't care what she is.

963
01:12:39,814 --> 01:12:44,318
抱歉，明白了，但你大错特错了，我赌60块你错了。
I'm sorry, clear, but you're very wrong, and I'll bet you $60 you're wrong.

964
01:12:44,443 --> 01:12:45,820
看。
Look.

965
01:12:45,945 --> 01:12:53,035
我正准备睡觉，突然发生了一件事……我不知道为什么我的心一分钟跑一英里。
I was getting ready to go to bed, and a certain matter came up... Why my heart should be going a mile a minute, I don't know.

966
01:12:53,953 --> 01:12:55,705
叫辆出租车，好吗?
Call a cab, will you?

967
01:12:57,498 --> 01:12:59,542
好吧，我自己叫。
All right, I'll call it myself.

968
01:13:01,669 --> 01:13:02,879
马里恩……
Marion...

969
01:13:05,047 --> 01:13:07,383
你就不能看着我，看清真相吗?
Can't you look at me and see the truth?

970
01:13:07,508 --> 01:13:10,219
我来得有点太早了。这是真相。
I arrived a little too soon. That's the truth.

971
01:13:10,344 --> 01:13:14,515
我让汉克开车从布伦特伍德送我回来因为我真的以为你需要我。
I had Hank drive me back from brentwood because I really thought you needed me.

972
01:13:14,640 --> 01:13:17,685
我真是太蠢了才会再考虑你，不是吗?
I'm all kinds of a fool to give you a second thought, aren't I?

973
01:13:17,810 --> 01:13:19,270
是的,是的。
Yeah, yeah.

974
01:13:20,104 --> 01:13:22,815
那你想从我这里得到什么?明亮的对话?
So what do you want from me? Bright dialogue?

975
01:13:22,940 --> 01:13:25,443
聪明机智的东西?
Something brilliant and witty?

976
01:13:28,237 --> 01:13:30,364
是什么让您这么着急呢?
What's your hurry?

977
01:13:31,324 --> 01:13:34,577
你可以随时叫出租车。你有一整晚的时间叫出租车!
You can call a cab anytime. You've got all night to call a cab!

978
01:13:35,411 --> 01:13:38,164
你是个很会戏剧性退场的小个子。
You're a great little one for dramatic exits.

979
01:13:38,289 --> 01:13:42,126
但我想这是我们的终点了。我们得把它摆到桌子上!
But I think this is the end of the line. We've got to get it out on the table!

980
01:13:42,251 --> 01:13:44,962
——坐下来。-不用了，谢谢。
- Sit down. - No, thank you.

981
01:13:45,087 --> 01:13:49,091
如果你以为我会留在这里听你的，那你就错了。
If you think I'm going to stay here and listen to you, you're mistaken.

982
01:13:49,216 --> 01:13:54,722
- - - - - -闭嘴!-我正要…让我说话。
- Shut up! - I've just about taken... Let me talk.

983
01:13:56,682 --> 01:14:01,062
别逼我回到我一贯的自我辩解的立场。
Don't push me back into my usual position of self-justification.

984
01:14:03,356 --> 01:14:12,198
现在，我们要扔掉一串烂葡萄那就是我，就是你感觉的我，但我得说，我觉得你的判断力很差。
For the time being, we'll throw away a bunch of rotten grapes that's me, that you seem to feel is me, though I must say, I think your judgment is lousy.

985
01:14:12,323 --> 01:14:15,284
你用锤子打我鼻子上的苍蝇!
You SWAT the fly on my nose with a hammer!

986
01:14:15,409 --> 01:14:16,452
扔掉它。
Throw it away.

987
01:14:16,577 --> 01:14:20,289
但我们每次谈话，都是关于查理·卡塞尔!
Yet every time we talk, it's about Charlie castle!

988
01:14:20,414 --> 01:14:26,754
从没提过他那长期受苦，多病的妻子，玛丽安。
Never once about his long-suffering, sickly wife, Marion.

989
01:14:28,673 --> 01:14:31,175
你知道你致命的错误在哪里吗?
Do you know where your fatal error lies?

990
01:14:31,300 --> 01:14:33,844
你应该知道，所以我来告诉你。
You ought to know, so I'm going to tell you.

991
01:14:33,970 --> 01:14:38,182
你被一种高尚的商人心理折磨着。
You're afflicted with a fine, fat case of merchant psychology.

992
01:14:38,307 --> 01:14:41,811
你讨价还价，玩弄你自己的本性。这是你的错误。
You bargain and trifle with your own nature. That's your error.

993
01:14:41,936 --> 01:14:46,148
今晚，你可能会毁了你的生活当然还有我的。
Tonight, you're about to possibly destroy your life and certainly mine.

994
01:14:47,149 --> 01:14:49,568
我们不是从无数人中挑出了彼此吗?
Didn't we pick each other out of millions?

995
01:14:49,694 --> 01:14:53,030
能不能像商人那样说:
Can this be bargained away by saying, like a merchant:

996
01:14:53,155 --> 01:14:59,704
"马里昂会做她自己，爱查理"除非他满足一定的价格和条件"
"Marion will be herself and love Charlie "only if he meets a certain price and conditions"?

997
01:15:02,915 --> 01:15:07,670
我所认识的那个富有而又充满爱心的女人呢?
Where's the rich, full-hearted woman I know you to be?

998
01:15:10,047 --> 01:15:18,139
我说，不要再讨价还价了，不要再提条件了，不要再提这种非此即彼的怪念头了，不要再把我们俩都勒死了。
I say no more bargains, no more conditions, no more of this either-or, neither-nor whim that strangles us both.

999
01:15:18,264 --> 01:15:22,268
我说不，我说不做我们自己!
I say no, and I say down with not being what we are!

1000
01:15:23,436 --> 01:15:25,062
你可以说话。
You can talk.

1001
01:15:25,187 --> 01:15:27,273
你可以说话。
You can talk.

1002
01:15:27,398 --> 01:15:30,776
当你是查理·凯斯时，你怎么能说话。
How you can talk when you're Charlie cass.

1003
01:15:31,569 --> 01:15:35,823
我想打败你，打败你……玛丽恩，我需要你。
I'd like to beat you, beat you... Marion, I need you.

1004
01:15:39,201 --> 01:15:40,578
我爱你。
I love you.

1005
01:15:42,955 --> 01:15:48,377
我保证理解你，奉献你，尽我所能。
I promise you understanding, devofion, anything I can give you.

1006
01:15:48,502 --> 01:15:51,881
听着，如果你离开我，祝你好运。
Listen, if you leave me, cross your fingers as you go.

1007
01:15:52,006 --> 01:15:54,675
事实上，为我祈祷吧。
In fact, pray for me.

1008
01:15:57,344 --> 01:15:59,055
但如果你留下来，就得是真的。
But if you stay, it's got to be real.

1009
01:15:59,180 --> 01:16:01,599
你不能再伸手去拿门把手了。
You've got to stop reaching for that doorknob.

1010
01:16:01,724 --> 01:16:05,770
你要爱我胜过爱你自己。
You've got to love me that much more than you do yourself.

1011
01:16:33,422 --> 01:16:35,132
谢谢你！
Thank you.

1012
01:16:37,301 --> 01:16:38,719
查理……
Charlie...

1013
01:16:41,555 --> 01:16:44,225
帮我个忙，好吗?
Do me a favor, will you?

1014
01:16:44,350 --> 01:16:46,894
趁还来得及，赶紧长大吧。
Grow up before it's too late.

1015
01:16:59,990 --> 01:17:02,409
再来一次，查理。
Just one more shot, Charlie.

1016
01:17:04,745 --> 01:17:07,706
-马上就来，汉库斯。——好的。
- Be with you in a minute, hankus. - All right.

1017
01:17:08,749 --> 01:17:12,044
——是的!谢谢你,查理。-谢谢，亲爱的。
- Yeah! Thanks, Charlie. - Thank you, honey.

1018
01:17:14,797 --> 01:17:18,425
所以你要离开我们所有人。回去写伟大的美国小说吗?
So you're leaving us all. Going back to write the great American novel?

1019
01:17:18,551 --> 01:17:20,719
好莱坞的损失，纽约的收获。
Hollywood's loss, New York's gain.

1020
01:17:20,845 --> 01:17:22,721
幸运的人。我有点羡慕你，汉克。
Lucky guy. I kind of envy you, Hank.

1021
01:17:22,847 --> 01:17:25,641
好吧，还有时间。局长是个大人物。
Well, there's still time. The chief's a big train.

1022
01:17:25,766 --> 01:17:28,269
要我帮你预订吗?
You want me to make reservations for you?

1023
01:17:28,394 --> 01:17:32,273
-这本书是关于什么的?——一个人。一个普通的人。
- What's the book is going to be about? - A man. An average man.

1024
01:17:32,398 --> 01:17:35,818
-一个非常像你的人。-是的，很普通。
- A man very much like you. - Yes, that's very average.

1025
01:17:35,943 --> 01:17:41,866
那么，一个人如何能成为一个受欢迎的电影明星，而不以某种方式反映平均水平呢?
Now, how could a man become a popular movie star without reflecting the average in one way or another?

1026
01:17:42,616 --> 01:17:44,660
真的是关于像我这样的人吗?
Is it really about a guy like me?

1027
01:17:45,911 --> 01:17:49,790
这是一个关于道德价值的寓言。
It's a fable, about moral values.

1028
01:17:49,915 --> 01:17:52,209
成功,幸福。
Success, happiness.

1029
01:17:53,586 --> 01:17:56,839
你觉得玛丽安在这里不会开心的，是吗?
You don't think Marion is going to be happy here, do you?

1030
01:17:56,964 --> 01:17:58,924
不，我觉得她不会高兴的。
No, I don't think she's going to be happy.

1031
01:17:59,049 --> 01:18:00,467
为什么不呢?
Why not?

1032
01:18:01,302 --> 01:18:04,263
因为你是个理想主义者，查理，你出卖了自己。
Because you were an idealist, Charlie, and you sold out.

1033
01:18:04,388 --> 01:18:09,059
你加入了hoff, coy & company，这让你变成了半个理想主义者。
You joined hoff, coy & company, and that left you half an idealist.

1034
01:18:09,185 --> 01:18:13,689
这世上没有比这更折磨人的了，无论是鱼还是鸟。
There's nothing more tortured on the face of this earth, neither fish nor fowl.

1035
01:18:13,814 --> 01:18:17,359
一个出卖了自己梦想的人，却无法忘记。
A man who's sold out his dreams, but he can't forget.

1036
01:18:17,484 --> 01:18:21,614
是啊，但这是有原因的，你没有掌握所有的事实。
Yeah, but there are reasons, pal. You don't have all the facts.

1037
01:18:21,739 --> 01:18:25,743
一个爱尔兰人写道:“我想我曾经把它送给过你，这是易卜生主义的精髓。”
An irishman wrote, I think I sent it to you once, the quintessence of ibsenism.

1038
01:18:25,868 --> 01:18:27,953
他说有三种人。
He said that there are three kinds of men.

1039
01:18:28,078 --> 01:18:31,832
首先,现实主义者。现在,忸怩作态。他和魔鬼做了交易。
First, the realist. Now, that's coy. He's made his deal with the devil.

1040
01:18:31,957 --> 01:18:33,876
他也不会有什么不同。
He wouldn't be any different.

1041
01:18:34,627 --> 01:18:39,089
还有个庸俗的人，像霍夫，跟他没什么不同。
Then there's the philistine, like hoff, who couldn't be any different.

1042
01:18:39,215 --> 01:18:43,427
但事实就是如此。他们有自己的正直，他们是清廉的。
But they are what they are. They have their own integrity, they're incorruptible.

1043
01:18:43,552 --> 01:18:46,472
然后是第三种，理想主义者。
Then there's the third kind, the idealist.

1044
01:18:46,597 --> 01:18:48,724
这是你的。
That was you.

1045
01:18:48,849 --> 01:18:52,436
查理，半理想主义是灵魂的腹膜炎。
Half-idealism, Charlie, is the peritonitis of the soul.

1046
01:18:56,941 --> 01:19:00,236
去写你的书吧，汉克。可耻的。
Go write your book, Hank. Make it scandalous.

1047
01:19:00,361 --> 01:19:03,155
你需要钱时随时给我电汇。
Wire me for money anytime you need it.

1048
01:19:03,280 --> 01:19:06,450
有人必须完成他生来就该做的工作。
Somebody has to complete the work he was born to do.

1049
01:19:08,535 --> 01:19:12,623
-我太天真了，不是吗?-是的，但这是你最好的品质之一。
- Naive, ain't I? - Yes, but it's one of your best qualities.

1050
01:19:13,540 --> 01:19:17,461
“灵魂腹膜炎。”这些都是你在地面上使用的词。
"Peritonitis of the soul." Those are the words you use above ground.

1051
01:19:20,256 --> 01:19:22,299
再见,汉克。
Goodbye, Hank.

1052
01:19:22,424 --> 01:19:23,842
再见,查理。
Goodbye, Charlie.

1053
01:19:25,010 --> 01:19:27,346
奋斗，你仍可能赢得祝福。
Struggle, you may still win a blessing.

1054
01:19:36,397 --> 01:19:40,359
- Coy先生，他一直在等你。-谢谢你，拉塞尔。
- Mr. Coy, he's been waiting for you. - Thank you, Russell.

1055
01:19:44,238 --> 01:19:45,906
嘿，凯蒂，怎么了?
Hey, kitty, what's up?

1056
01:19:46,031 --> 01:19:48,784
你在哪里?我到处找你。
Where you been? I've been looking everywhere for you.

1057
01:19:48,909 --> 01:19:50,786
奇怪的是，我去过演播室。
Oddly enough, I've been at the studio.

1058
01:19:50,911 --> 01:19:54,081
一些剧照，我想和一位作家朋友说再见。
Some stills, and I wanted to say goodbye to a writer friend.

1059
01:19:54,206 --> 01:19:56,125
——绞盘机?-是的。
- Teagle? - Yeah.

1060
01:19:56,250 --> 01:20:00,254
我以为他回纽约了。我在想他的名字。
I thought he went back to New York. I'm trying to remember his first name.

1061
01:20:00,379 --> 01:20:01,880
荷瑞修。
Horatio.

1062
01:20:02,006 --> 01:20:05,217
-他为我们写过什么?-屏幕上什么都没有。
- What did he ever write for us? - Nothing that got on the screen.

1063
01:20:05,342 --> 01:20:08,762
斯坦利永远不明白他的剧本是关于什么的。
Stanley could never understand what his scripts were about.

1064
01:20:12,558 --> 01:20:14,893
查理，有事情发生了，很热的事情。
Charlie, something's come up, something hot.

1065
01:20:15,019 --> 01:20:18,605
-我告诉纳特我不会去演那个音乐剧的!-和音乐剧无关。
- I told nat I wouldn't do that musical! - Nothing to do with the musical.

1066
01:20:18,731 --> 01:20:21,275
斯坦利对迪克西·埃文斯大发雷霆。
Stanley blew his top with Dixie Evans.

1067
01:20:21,400 --> 01:20:24,236
他请她今天下午来谈一谈。
He asked her to come in this afternoon and have a talk.

1068
01:20:24,361 --> 01:20:28,741
她迟到了一个小时，喝得醉醺醺的，还用皮带牵着一条狗。
She showed up one hour late, drunk, lugging a dog on a leash.

1069
01:20:28,866 --> 01:20:30,743
贵宾犬吗?
A poodle?

1070
01:20:30,868 --> 01:20:34,705
情况已经够严重了，史丹利忍住了怒气。
The situation being serious enough, Stanley kept his temper.

1071
01:20:34,830 --> 01:20:38,751
他像父亲一样对她说话。他说……让我告诉你他说了什么。
He talked to her like a father. He said... Let me tell you what he said.

1072
01:20:38,876 --> 01:20:40,919
他告诉她他在贝永擦皮鞋的日子。
He told her about his bootblack days in bayonne.

1073
01:20:41,045 --> 01:20:47,426
然后，他轻轻地哼了一声“心神不安”的曲子，然后，在你还不知道发生了什么事之前，他已经泪流满面了。
Then he chimed softly the "uneasy lies the head" routine, then, before you knew what was happening, he made with the tears.

1074
01:20:48,886 --> 01:20:52,097
-然后呢?-她当面嘲笑他。
- Then what happened? - She laughed in his face.

1075
01:20:52,222 --> 01:20:54,475
告诉他全镇的人都知道他哭了。
Told him the whole town knew about his crying.

1076
01:20:54,600 --> 01:20:57,102
是时候改弦更张了。
It was time to change the act.

1077
01:20:58,062 --> 01:20:59,480
他打她吗?
He hit her?

1078
01:20:59,605 --> 01:21:02,441
把她打倒在地，踢得青一块紫一块。
Knocked her down and kicked her black and blue.

1079
01:21:03,400 --> 01:21:08,238
可能断了一根肋骨。他们把她绑在医务室里。
May have broken one of her ribs. They taped her up in the infirmary.

1080
01:21:09,281 --> 01:21:16,455
我们的故事是，那只大怪物之一的狗，猛地一拉皮带，把她扔在地上。
Our story is that the dog, one of those great big monsters, yanked on the leash and threw her to the floor.

1081
01:21:16,580 --> 01:21:23,504
她知道她没法让袭击的故事站得住脚，但是…她说她准备把你的故事告诉媒体。
She knows she can't make an assault story stick, but... She says she's ready to spill your story to the press.

1082
01:21:23,629 --> 01:21:25,631
尤其是帕蒂本笃。
Particularly Patty Benedict.

1083
01:21:25,756 --> 01:21:29,802
这就是爱，这就是爱，我
.I that's love, that's love...I

1084
01:21:35,391 --> 01:21:38,185
-她在哪儿?-施瓦布对面的酒吧。
- Where is she? - That bar across from schwab's.

1085
01:21:38,310 --> 01:21:40,896
一个女人喝六杯马提尼酒能毁了一座城市。
A woman with six martinis can ruin a city.

1086
01:21:43,440 --> 01:21:47,277
-你在笑什么?-我在笑吗?
- What are you smiling about? - Am I smiling?

1087
01:21:50,280 --> 01:21:54,785
嗯…我们的下一个议程是什么?
Well... what's next on our sordid agenda?

1088
01:21:54,910 --> 01:21:57,371
得有人给马装上马鞍。
Somebody's got to saddle the horse.

1089
01:21:59,081 --> 01:22:01,542
快过去把她带出酒吧。
Get over there and get her out of that bar.

1090
01:22:01,667 --> 01:22:03,252
-带她去哪里?——她的公寓。
- Get her to where? - Her apartment.

1091
01:22:03,377 --> 01:22:06,046
——为什么是我?-你是她唯一的舞伴。
- Why me? - You're the only one she'll go with.

1092
01:22:06,171 --> 01:22:07,840
别担心电话。
Don't worry about the telephone.

1093
01:22:07,965 --> 01:22:10,843
我们已经处理好了。这是拽。
We've taken care of that. It's been yanked.

1094
01:22:10,968 --> 01:22:13,762
喂她一些马提尼酒。那会让她安静下来的。
Feed her some martinis. That'll keep her quiet.

1095
01:22:15,639 --> 01:22:19,810
-如果他们没有呢?——他们会。杜松子酒的窜改。
- Suppose they don't? - They will. The gin's doctored.

1096
01:22:29,445 --> 01:22:32,990
好了，她躺在地板上。现在我该怎么办?
Okay, she's on the floor. Now what do I do?

1097
01:22:33,115 --> 01:22:36,702
等她晕过去就离开。从那一刻起，你就清白了。
Leave the minute she passes out. From that moment on, you're in the clear.

1098
01:22:36,827 --> 01:22:38,579
回演播室报到。
Report back to the studio.

1099
01:22:38,704 --> 01:22:41,915
你一整天都在做宣传照。
You've been there all day long making publicity stills.

1100
01:22:53,802 --> 01:23:00,809
笑脸……你的话里有毛。你脑子里全是虱子。
Smiley... Your words have hair on them. Your brain is full of lice.

1101
01:23:00,934 --> 01:23:03,604
相信我,查理。没时间了。
Trust me, Charlie. There's no time to lose.

1102
01:23:03,729 --> 01:23:05,397
只要记住一件事。
Just bear in mind one thing.

1103
01:23:05,522 --> 01:23:10,944
你第一次策划的那天，你就把策划和策划的孩子们结合起来。
The day you first scheme, you marry that scheme and the scheme's children.

1104
01:23:11,069 --> 01:23:15,657
这一分钟你想要的一切都取决于荡妇肚子里的几杯酒。
Everything you want this minute depends on a few drinks in a trollop's guts.

1105
01:23:16,575 --> 01:23:20,120
你觉得她是什么人?飞蛾? 虫子？
What do you think she is? A moth? A bug?

1106
01:23:20,245 --> 01:23:23,874
说话轻松。保持灵活,基蒂。
Speak easy. Keep flexible, kitty.

1107
01:23:24,833 --> 01:23:28,462
这周末她就会被遗忘。
She'll go unremembered by the end of the week.

1108
01:23:31,673 --> 01:23:33,675
——斯坦利在哪儿?-他不知道这件事
- Where's Stanley? - He doesn't know about this.

1109
01:23:33,800 --> 01:23:37,638
那我们就得告诉他，对吧?你去找他，斯迈利。我要回去了。
Then we'll have to tell him, won't we? You find him, smiley. I'll get back nat.

1110
01:23:37,763 --> 01:23:39,598
没有理由让他们参与进来。
There's no reason for them to be involved.

1111
01:23:39,723 --> 01:23:43,227
但我有足够的理由比以前更深入地参与进来?
But there's plenty of reason for me to be involved even deeper than before?

1112
01:23:43,352 --> 01:23:46,855
我不会那么做的，凯蒂。别再提高嗓门了。
I wouldn't do that, kitty. And don't raise your voice again.

1113
01:23:46,980 --> 01:23:48,649
你不记得了吗?
Don't you remember?

1114
01:23:48,774 --> 01:23:51,443
我是“抱着渺茫希望的武士吟游诗人”。
I'm the "warrior minstrel with the forlorn hope".

1115
01:23:55,906 --> 01:23:58,492
-对不起，我不是故意打扰你的。-没事的。
- Sorry, I didn't mean to interrupt. - It's all right.

1116
01:23:58,617 --> 01:24:00,536
——你好,马里昂。——你好,笑脸。
- Hello, Marion. - Hello, smiley.

1117
01:24:00,661 --> 01:24:03,038
我去厨房拿外套。
I'll get my coat from the kitchen.

1118
01:24:05,624 --> 01:24:07,876
-她在这里做什么?——廉价农奴劳动力。
- What's she doing here? - Cheap serf labor.

1119
01:24:08,001 --> 01:24:10,837
-我付她一辈子的钱。-那天晚上你们分居了
- I pay her by the lifetime. - You were separated the other night.

1120
01:24:10,963 --> 01:24:14,007
我等待。拿着图书馆的电话，把那个催泪器拿来。
I'm waiting. Take that library phone and get that weeper here.

1121
01:24:14,132 --> 01:24:17,052
好吧。如果我不能指望你，我就自己处理。
Okay. If I can't count on you, I'll handle this myself.

1122
01:24:17,177 --> 01:24:21,306
哦,不。谋杀是不可分割的。我发现了，就像贞操一样。
Oh, no. Murder is indivisible. I'm finding that out, like chastity.

1123
01:24:21,431 --> 01:24:24,031
没有小量这回事。我也在寻找答案。
There's no such thing as a small amount. I'm finding that out too.

1124
01:24:24,142 --> 01:24:27,688
-别吹你的假发，学者-给我接通斯坦利·霍夫!
- Don't blow your wig, scholar. - Get me Stanley hoff!

1125
01:24:28,605 --> 01:24:31,900
-好吧，我自己来。-别孩子气了，查理。
- All right, I'll do it myself. - Don't be boyish, Charlie.

1126
01:24:32,025 --> 01:24:34,185
你觉得你能把斯坦利牵扯进来吗?
You think you can involve Stanley in a thing like this?

1127
01:24:34,278 --> 01:24:38,407
-他已经忙得不可开交了。——证明了这一点。试着证明它。
- He's already involved up to his neck. - Prove it. Try and prove it.

1128
01:24:39,283 --> 01:24:42,786
为了你自己，这不关别人的事，甚至不关你妻子的事。
For your own sake, this is nobody else's business, not even your wife's.

1129
01:24:42,911 --> 01:24:45,330
马里恩!马里恩!
Marion! Marion!

1130
01:24:45,455 --> 01:24:48,208
Smiley coy有话要跟你说!
Smiley coy wants to tell you something!

1131
01:24:48,333 --> 01:24:50,752
凯蒂，我觉得你真的心动了。
Kitty, I think you've really flipped.

1132
01:24:52,588 --> 01:24:56,049
-玛丽恩，查理喝醉了。-继续，告诉她，笑嘻嘻。
- Marion, Charlie's drunk. - Go on, tell her, smiley.

1133
01:24:56,174 --> 01:24:57,968
去告诉她吧!
Go ahead and tell her!

1134
01:24:58,093 --> 01:25:01,138
凯蒂，别那么急躁。小心你的步骤。
Now, don't be impetuous, kitty. Watch your step.

1135
01:25:02,139 --> 01:25:04,808
查理今天还没清醒到讨论剧本的程度。
Charlie's not sober enough to discuss the script today.

1136
01:25:04,933 --> 01:25:06,977
我掌握了一些事实。
I have certain facts in my hands.

1137
01:25:07,102 --> 01:25:10,397
如果他们被炸飞了，我就只剩下流血的残肢而不是手。
If they blow up, I've got bleeding stumps left not hands.

1138
01:25:10,522 --> 01:25:12,608
但你也要去。
But you'll go, too.

1139
01:25:12,733 --> 01:25:14,776
我是查理·卡塞尔，斯坦利·霍夫。
This is Charlie castle for Stanley hoff.

1140
01:25:14,901 --> 01:25:17,821
-查理，怎么了?-你会告诉她吗?
- Charlie, what is it? - Are you going to tell her?

1141
01:25:17,946 --> 01:25:21,700
玛丽安，查理对他的朋友有很多幻想。
Marion, Charlie gets fanciful ideas about his friend.

1142
01:25:21,825 --> 01:25:30,542
他实际上是在指控我密谋谋杀一个录音室的小演员那个人在事故当晚和他一起在车里。
He's actually accusing me of plotting the murder of a little studio bit player who was with him in the car the night of the accident.

1143
01:25:33,045 --> 01:25:35,339
玛丽恩，我稍后再解释。
I'll explain later, Marion.

1144
01:25:35,464 --> 01:25:38,925
请拿着图书馆的电话，马上把纳特叫来。
Please, take the library phone and get nat here right away.

1145
01:25:42,095 --> 01:25:44,640
也许你知道自己在做什么。
Maybe you know what you're doing.

1146
01:25:44,765 --> 01:25:47,893
-我想我会等。-我知道你会等的。
- I think I'll wait. - I know you'll wait.

1147
01:25:48,018 --> 01:25:50,062
你会等啊等啊等。
You'll wait and wait and wait.

1148
01:25:51,271 --> 01:25:55,275
-你对待你的朋友很糟糕，凯蒂。-你不是我的朋友。
- You mishandle your friends, kitty. - You're not my friend.

1149
01:25:55,400 --> 01:25:57,861
那个可怜的小女孩是我的朋友。
That pathetic little girl is my friend.

1150
01:25:58,987 --> 01:26:03,909
——莉莉?霍夫叔叔，请说。你能马上过来吗?
- Lily? Uncle hoff, if you please. - Could you come over right away?

1151
01:26:06,411 --> 01:26:10,582
我知道我不只是在表达我的观点，也是你的观点。
I know I'm not only expressing my views, but yours as well.

1152
01:26:10,707 --> 01:26:17,881
至于你关于暴力和犯罪的含笑的想法，我对你的想法很尊重，但我不相信。
As for your idea that smiley coy thought in terms of violence and crime, with all due respect to what you thought, I can't give it credence.

1153
01:26:18,006 --> 01:26:21,218
你是说笑脸什么都没告诉我。我只是凭空想象出来的。
You're saying smiley didn't tell me anything. I just dreamed it up.

1154
01:26:21,343 --> 01:26:25,263
我不会说你白天做梦，但喝了几杯之后，这可能吗?
I wouldn't say you dream by day, but after a few drinks, isn't it possible?

1155
01:26:25,389 --> 01:26:27,808
什么是可能的，这正是我所说的。
What is possible is exactly what I said.

1156
01:26:28,934 --> 01:26:31,395
-让我把我的想法讲清楚。-不要把他们围起来。
- Let me round out my thoughts. - Don't round them out.

1157
01:26:31,520 --> 01:26:33,355
-我可以继续…-我不希望你这么做
- I may continue... - I don't want you to.

1158
01:26:33,480 --> 01:26:39,319
你永远不会被告知，你演讲时的刺绣与你要说的任何话完全不成比例。
